WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
الحمد بالله رب العالمين

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:07.000
الرحمن الرحيم

00:00:07.000 --> 00:00:10.000
مالك يوم الدين

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:14.000
إياك نعبد وإياك نستعيم

00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:18.000
اهدن الصراق المستقيم

00:00:18.000 --> 00:00:21.000
صراق الذين أنعنت عليهم

00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:24.000
غير المرضوب عليهم

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:35.230
السلام عليكم و رحمة الله و بركاته

00:00:35.230 --> 00:00:37.230
بسم الله الرحمن الرحيم

00:00:37.230 --> 00:00:39.230
الحمد لله رب العالمين و بهم نستعين

00:00:39.230 --> 00:00:42.230
و نصلي و نسلم على أفضل الخلق أجمعين

00:00:42.230 --> 00:00:46.230
نبينا محمد و على آله و صحبه و التابعين

00:00:46.230 --> 00:00:50.230
و من تبعهم بإحسان إلى يوم الدين و بعد

00:00:50.230 --> 00:00:54.230
We commence as always by praising Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:00:54.230 --> 00:00:58.230
sending complete blessings and salutations upon the masterpiece

00:00:58.230 --> 00:01:00.230
محمد ابن عبد الله

00:01:00.230 --> 00:01:04.230
May Allah's peace and blessings be upon him, his entire household

00:01:04.230 --> 00:01:05.230
and all his companions

00:01:05.230 --> 00:01:07.230
and may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala bless them all

00:01:07.230 --> 00:01:09.230
and may he bless every single one of us

00:01:09.230 --> 00:01:10.230
and grant us goodness

00:01:10.230 --> 00:01:13.230
Beloved brothers and sisters in Islam

00:01:13.230 --> 00:01:15.230
It is important that before we commence

00:01:15.230 --> 00:01:17.230
we make mention of a few points

00:01:17.230 --> 00:01:22.230
regarding the seerah or the life of Rasulullah صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:01:22.230 --> 00:01:24.230
There are many books that have been compiled

00:01:24.230 --> 00:01:27.230
about the life of Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:01:27.230 --> 00:01:30.230
Some of them are in a story form

00:01:30.230 --> 00:01:33.230
and some of them are in narration form

00:01:33.230 --> 00:01:36.230
Some of them have made mention of just a story

00:01:36.230 --> 00:01:38.230
so from the beginning to the end

00:01:38.230 --> 00:01:41.230
according to some chronological order

00:01:41.230 --> 00:01:44.230
the story is mentioned so people can read it

00:01:44.230 --> 00:01:47.230
and they can learn a lesson from it and understand it

00:01:47.230 --> 00:01:49.230
But if we were to look deeper

00:01:49.230 --> 00:01:52.230
we would find that those who have written it in story form

00:01:52.230 --> 00:01:55.230
they have gathered it from somewhere

00:01:55.230 --> 00:01:58.230
where narrations have been made mention of

00:01:58.230 --> 00:02:01.230
Some of these narrations are made mention of

00:02:01.230 --> 00:02:04.230
by companions of Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:02:04.230 --> 00:02:06.230
and some of them by historians

00:02:06.230 --> 00:02:09.230
Now you and I know that in Islam

00:02:09.230 --> 00:02:11.230
whenever we want to utter something

00:02:11.230 --> 00:02:14.230
we need to ensure that we have a chain of narrators

00:02:14.230 --> 00:02:17.230
going back to the source of the story

00:02:17.230 --> 00:02:19.230
to Rasulullah صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:02:19.230 --> 00:02:22.230
or to the one whom it had happened to

00:02:22.230 --> 00:02:24.230
So we will find exactly how it happened

00:02:24.230 --> 00:02:27.230
If there is a problem in the chain of narrators

00:02:27.230 --> 00:02:30.230
nowadays it is very very easy to tell

00:02:30.230 --> 00:02:33.230
this is a weak narration and that is a correct narration

00:02:33.230 --> 00:02:35.230
authentic narration and so on

00:02:35.230 --> 00:02:39.230
because we have all the data in a small little chip

00:02:39.230 --> 00:02:42.230
or in a disk or on a website

00:02:42.230 --> 00:02:44.230
if we would know how to search

00:02:44.230 --> 00:02:47.230
we would be able to look if someone is telling a lie or not

00:02:47.230 --> 00:02:50.230
because it's quite easy to find out

00:02:50.230 --> 00:02:53.230
that this person is claiming to have heard from someone

00:02:53.230 --> 00:02:55.230
who died before they were born

00:02:55.230 --> 00:02:56.230
so that's a lie

00:02:56.230 --> 00:02:59.230
or this person is claiming to have heard from someone

00:02:59.230 --> 00:03:02.230
who never ever visited them and they did not visit them

00:03:02.230 --> 00:03:04.230
so you would know there is a problem there

00:03:04.230 --> 00:03:07.230
or there is a person who is narrating

00:03:07.230 --> 00:03:09.230
and he is saying that I heard from so and so

00:03:09.230 --> 00:03:12.230
but he was known amongst his people as a liar

00:03:12.230 --> 00:03:16.230
in that particular case we cannot base our deen on that

00:03:16.230 --> 00:03:18.230
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness

00:03:18.230 --> 00:03:21.230
So what I have tried to do is

00:03:21.230 --> 00:03:23.230
to make mention of that which is authentic

00:03:23.230 --> 00:03:26.230
and as you know as days pass

00:03:26.230 --> 00:03:28.230
we authenticate even more

00:03:28.230 --> 00:03:31.230
and if it is found that we have also said something

00:03:31.230 --> 00:03:32.230
which is not authentic

00:03:32.230 --> 00:03:35.230
then we would revise it to excuse ourselves

00:03:35.230 --> 00:03:37.230
to say this is not authentic

00:03:37.230 --> 00:03:40.230
or we found that this was not correct and so on

00:03:40.230 --> 00:03:42.230
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala bless us

00:03:42.230 --> 00:03:43.230
The reason I say this

00:03:43.230 --> 00:03:45.230
Muhammad salallahu alayhi wasalam

00:03:45.230 --> 00:03:47.230
is the highest of creation

00:03:47.230 --> 00:03:48.230
We don't doubt that

00:03:48.230 --> 00:03:50.230
He is the most blessed

00:03:50.230 --> 00:03:52.230
He is the most honoured

00:03:52.230 --> 00:03:55.230
He was loved and favoured by Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala the most

00:03:56.230 --> 00:03:59.230
but he is still a creature of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:03:59.230 --> 00:04:01.230
the highest of all creatures

00:04:01.230 --> 00:04:03.230
We know he has the highest status

00:04:03.230 --> 00:04:06.230
with the truth that we know about him

00:04:06.230 --> 00:04:07.230
So why should we lie?

00:04:07.230 --> 00:04:09.230
In order to raise his status

00:04:09.230 --> 00:04:13.230
Do you think lies is going to make him any more important?

00:04:13.230 --> 00:04:15.230
When he is already the most important?

00:04:15.230 --> 00:04:17.230
So there is no point to lie

00:04:17.230 --> 00:04:19.230
Sometimes people have a disease

00:04:19.230 --> 00:04:21.230
When we tell them this is wrong

00:04:21.230 --> 00:04:24.230
They automatically start getting excited and angry

00:04:24.230 --> 00:04:25.230
To say no, no, no

00:04:25.230 --> 00:04:27.230
You have blasphemed and you have done this

00:04:27.230 --> 00:04:28.230
No, that's not the case

00:04:28.230 --> 00:04:31.230
Nobody is denying that he is the highest

00:04:31.230 --> 00:04:33.230
Nobody is denying his status

00:04:33.230 --> 00:04:37.230
Nobody is denying that Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala has favoured him

00:04:37.230 --> 00:04:38.230
But all we are saying is

00:04:38.230 --> 00:04:40.230
This is an authentic narration

00:04:40.230 --> 00:04:42.230
It has been made mention of

00:04:42.230 --> 00:04:44.230
And what others are making mention of

00:04:44.230 --> 00:04:47.230
Is either fabricated or is not as authentic

00:04:47.230 --> 00:04:49.230
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala bless us

00:04:49.230 --> 00:04:53.230
Remember the winner is he who follows that example

00:04:53.230 --> 00:04:56.230
The winner is not he who barks all day and night

00:04:56.230 --> 00:04:59.230
The winner is the one who follows the example

00:04:59.230 --> 00:05:00.230
You know they say

00:05:00.230 --> 00:05:02.230
Put your money where your mouth is

00:05:02.230 --> 00:05:03.230
Allahu Akbar

00:05:03.230 --> 00:05:04.230
Which means you want to talk big

00:05:04.230 --> 00:05:05.230
Put it, let's see

00:05:05.230 --> 00:05:07.230
May Allah protect us

00:05:07.230 --> 00:05:10.230
May we not be from amongst those who pay lip service

00:05:10.230 --> 00:05:12.230
Without following his example

00:05:12.230 --> 00:05:14.230
Without emanating what he has come with

00:05:14.230 --> 00:05:17.230
May we not be from amongst those who claim to be his followers yet

00:05:17.230 --> 00:05:18.230
We don't read Salah

00:05:18.230 --> 00:05:22.230
We have bad habits of adultery, fornication, gambling, smoking and so on

00:05:22.230 --> 00:05:25.230
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala protect us from such habits

00:05:25.230 --> 00:05:28.230
I see the brothers are frowning at me when I said smoking

00:05:28.230 --> 00:05:29.230
Don't we agree it's a bad habit?

00:05:29.230 --> 00:05:30.230
Come on

00:05:30.230 --> 00:05:31.230
Month of Ramadan

00:05:31.230 --> 00:05:35.230
Can't we give up one major bad habit of ours every Ramadan?

00:05:35.230 --> 00:05:38.230
Wallahi we would be from amongst those who've given up

00:05:38.230 --> 00:05:40.230
30, 40 bad habits by now

00:05:40.230 --> 00:05:44.230
If we just gave up one major habit every Ramadan

00:05:44.230 --> 00:05:45.230
When the doctor tells you

00:05:45.230 --> 00:05:47.230
Listen, you've got to give up smoking

00:05:47.230 --> 00:05:49.230
Because if not this will happen, that will happen

00:05:49.230 --> 00:05:50.230
We throw it out

00:05:50.230 --> 00:05:51.230
We know it's a bad habit

00:05:51.230 --> 00:05:54.230
We're not talking about haram and halal and makruh and so on

00:05:54.230 --> 00:05:56.230
We're talking of whether it's a good habit or not

00:05:56.230 --> 00:05:59.230
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala empower us

00:05:59.230 --> 00:06:03.230
To understand that following the example of Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:06:03.230 --> 00:06:06.230
Requires willpower, it requires iman

00:06:06.230 --> 00:06:08.230
It requires a genuine iman

00:06:08.230 --> 00:06:13.230
And the understanding of the seerah of Rasulullah sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:06:13.230 --> 00:06:15.230
So I'd like to start off by saying that

00:06:15.230 --> 00:06:19.230
It was brought to my notice that yesterday and perhaps previously

00:06:19.230 --> 00:06:23.230
On some occasions instead of saying 5 years from the prophethood

00:06:23.230 --> 00:06:25.230
I said 5 years of hijra

00:06:25.230 --> 00:06:27.230
And I'm sure you would have picked that up

00:06:27.230 --> 00:06:30.230
Like when I made mention of the marriage of Sauda binti Zam'ah

00:06:30.230 --> 00:06:31.230
Radhiallahu anha

00:06:31.230 --> 00:06:34.230
By mistake I said 10th Hijri

00:06:34.230 --> 00:06:37.230
And I said that's the same year that Khadija binti Khuwalid

00:06:37.230 --> 00:06:39.230
Radhiallahu anha passed away

00:06:39.230 --> 00:06:42.230
Well you would understand that that was 10 years from prophethood

00:06:42.230 --> 00:06:45.230
Because hijra had not yet taken place

00:06:45.230 --> 00:06:46.230
That was just a slip of the tongue

00:06:46.230 --> 00:06:49.230
I thought it was only correct for me to correct that

00:06:49.230 --> 00:06:52.230
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness

00:06:52.230 --> 00:06:56.230
We had also made mention of the way Sa'd ibn Mu'adh

00:06:56.230 --> 00:06:59.230
One of the leaders of Aws had accepted Islam

00:06:59.230 --> 00:07:02.230
When Mus'ab ibn Umayr was there with As'ad ibn Zurara

00:07:02.230 --> 00:07:04.230
Radhiallahu anhum

00:07:04.230 --> 00:07:07.230
And we made mention of how Usayid ibn Hudayr

00:07:07.230 --> 00:07:10.230
Radhiallahu anhu had gone up to them trying to stop them

00:07:10.230 --> 00:07:13.230
And when Mus'ab ibn Umayr spoke to him

00:07:13.230 --> 00:07:14.230
He accepted Islam

00:07:14.230 --> 00:07:17.230
Moments later the same happened with Sa'd ibn Mu'adh

00:07:17.230 --> 00:07:21.230
There is a point of detail that is important for me to mention

00:07:21.230 --> 00:07:22.230
And that is

00:07:22.230 --> 00:07:25.230
When Sa'd ibn Mu'adh accepted Islam

00:07:25.230 --> 00:07:28.230
He got up to his clan

00:07:28.230 --> 00:07:29.230
Who were they?

00:07:29.230 --> 00:07:32.230
They were known as Banu Abdul Ashhal

00:07:32.230 --> 00:07:34.230
He got up to them and he said

00:07:34.230 --> 00:07:35.230
Oh Banu Abdul Ashhal

00:07:35.230 --> 00:07:37.230
I am not going to speak to any one of you

00:07:37.230 --> 00:07:38.230
Neither male nor female

00:07:38.230 --> 00:07:41.230
Until you accept this man as a messenger

00:07:41.230 --> 00:07:43.230
They all accepted without exception

00:07:43.230 --> 00:07:44.230
Subhanallah

00:07:44.230 --> 00:07:46.230
So this shows when the chief accepts

00:07:46.230 --> 00:07:47.230
The rest of them follow

00:07:47.230 --> 00:07:50.230
This was Sa'd ibn Mu'adh radhiallahu anhu

00:07:50.230 --> 00:07:54.230
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us a lesson from his entire life

00:07:54.230 --> 00:07:56.230
We will come back to this man insha'Allah

00:07:56.230 --> 00:07:58.230
When we make mention of the wars

00:07:58.230 --> 00:08:02.230
That took place at the time of Rasulullah sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:08:02.230 --> 00:08:05.230
Then there is an important story that we touched on

00:08:05.230 --> 00:08:07.230
And I think we need to mention a little bit of detail

00:08:07.230 --> 00:08:10.230
The marriage of Rasulullah sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:08:10.230 --> 00:08:11.230
To Aisha radhiallahu anha

00:08:12.230 --> 00:08:14.230
Khawla binti Hakim radhiallahu anha

00:08:14.230 --> 00:08:17.230
Had made mention to Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:08:17.230 --> 00:08:19.230
Of marrying Sawda binti Zam'a

00:08:19.230 --> 00:08:22.230
And she also made mention of marrying Aisha

00:08:22.230 --> 00:08:26.230
The daughter of your best friend or messenger sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:08:26.230 --> 00:08:28.230
So she went to Um Ruman

00:08:28.230 --> 00:08:35.230
Who was the wife of Abu Bakr as-Siddiq radhiallahu anhu

00:08:35.230 --> 00:08:38.230
Khawla binti Hakim went to her and made the suggestion

00:08:38.230 --> 00:08:40.230
She spoke to Abu Bakr as-Siddiq radhiallahu anhu

00:08:40.230 --> 00:08:42.230
And they agreed, subhanallah, they were happy

00:08:42.230 --> 00:08:46.230
They were happy although initially Abu Bakr as-Siddiq radhiallahu anhu

00:08:46.230 --> 00:08:47.230
Made mention of a point

00:08:47.230 --> 00:08:49.230
He said when this girl was young

00:08:49.230 --> 00:08:52.230
I had promised her to Jubair ibn al-Mut'im ibn Adi

00:08:52.230 --> 00:08:56.230
And this man is still a mushrik, let me go to them and see

00:08:56.230 --> 00:09:01.230
When he went to Al-Mut'im ibn Adi, the father of Jubair

00:09:01.230 --> 00:09:04.230
And spoke to him and his wife

00:09:04.230 --> 00:09:06.230
The wife quickly uttered words

00:09:06.230 --> 00:09:10.230
That my son is not going to leave the religion of his forefathers

00:09:10.230 --> 00:09:12.230
In order to marry your daughter

00:09:12.230 --> 00:09:16.230
And from this Abu Bakr radhiallahu anhu was quite delighted

00:09:16.230 --> 00:09:19.230
Because obviously as we said it served his purpose

00:09:19.230 --> 00:09:23.230
So he went away and basically the engagement was broken

00:09:23.230 --> 00:09:26.230
So she was more or less fixed to someone

00:09:26.230 --> 00:09:28.230
And as we said up to today

00:09:28.230 --> 00:09:31.230
There are people who fix up their little children in marriage

00:09:31.230 --> 00:09:32.230
From a very young age

00:09:32.230 --> 00:09:35.230
I'm sure you have come across some of these incidents

00:09:35.230 --> 00:09:38.230
Perhaps the new generation might not have heard about it

00:09:38.230 --> 00:09:40.230
Ask your parents, they will tell you it's true

00:09:40.230 --> 00:09:43.230
And sometimes nowadays people mention it jokingly

00:09:43.230 --> 00:09:45.230
Before it was serious

00:09:45.230 --> 00:09:47.230
If they had said this, that's it

00:09:47.230 --> 00:09:49.230
When you grow old, you know what happens?

00:09:49.230 --> 00:09:51.230
You got to get married exactly where your parents wanted

00:09:51.230 --> 00:09:53.230
You had no say in it

00:09:53.230 --> 00:09:55.230
Unless you rejected

00:09:55.230 --> 00:09:57.230
But you could not come and say no, no, no

00:09:57.230 --> 00:09:59.230
I want to get married there

00:09:59.230 --> 00:10:01.230
You had to get married where they wanted

00:10:01.230 --> 00:10:03.230
If not, they would choose another place for you

00:10:03.230 --> 00:10:05.230
If not, they would choose a third place for you

00:10:05.230 --> 00:10:07.230
And it was always them who chose

00:10:07.230 --> 00:10:10.230
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us the understanding

00:10:10.230 --> 00:10:14.230
May He make us understand also the happiness of our parents

00:10:14.230 --> 00:10:16.230
And at the same time may He make us parents

00:10:16.230 --> 00:10:19.230
Who also look at the happiness of our own children

00:10:19.230 --> 00:10:21.230
Because wallahi, it is a give and take

00:10:21.230 --> 00:10:24.230
In the sense that we need to understand what Allah wants

00:10:24.230 --> 00:10:26.230
And we need to understand what is good for us

00:10:26.230 --> 00:10:28.230
If parents are wrong, they would be wrong

00:10:28.230 --> 00:10:30.230
And if children are wrong, they would be wrong

00:10:30.230 --> 00:10:32.230
Because what is right is adopting

00:10:32.230 --> 00:10:34.230
The Sunnah of Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:10:34.230 --> 00:10:36.230
So Aisha radiallahu anha

00:10:36.230 --> 00:10:40.230
She was married to Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:10:40.230 --> 00:10:41.230
When she was very young

00:10:41.230 --> 00:10:43.230
Narrations make mention of the age of 6

00:10:43.230 --> 00:10:45.230
And some make mention of the age of 7

00:10:45.230 --> 00:10:48.230
And this means that the aqid

00:10:48.230 --> 00:10:51.230
Or the solemnization of the nikah was done

00:10:51.230 --> 00:10:53.230
But they did not live together

00:10:53.230 --> 00:10:55.230
She was still in the house of her father

00:10:55.230 --> 00:10:57.230
Until after they got to Madina Munawwarah

00:10:57.230 --> 00:10:59.230
And thereafter after some time

00:10:59.230 --> 00:11:01.230
They lived together

00:11:01.230 --> 00:11:03.230
But this point was very important

00:11:03.230 --> 00:11:05.230
Because a lot of people question

00:11:05.230 --> 00:11:07.230
The age of Aisha radiallahu anha

00:11:07.230 --> 00:11:09.230
How can this be?

00:11:09.230 --> 00:11:10.230
And how bad is the messenger?

00:11:10.230 --> 00:11:12.230
Astaghfirullah, a'udhu billah

00:11:12.230 --> 00:11:13.230
How bad would he have been

00:11:13.230 --> 00:11:15.230
In order to have done this?

00:11:15.230 --> 00:11:17.230
Wallahi, there is nothing bad about it

00:11:17.230 --> 00:11:19.230
It was the norm of the time

00:11:19.230 --> 00:11:20.230
And at the same time

00:11:20.230 --> 00:11:23.230
It was more of what we would term today

00:11:23.230 --> 00:11:25.230
We nowadays term an engagement

00:11:25.230 --> 00:11:27.230
As people having been fixed

00:11:27.230 --> 00:11:28.230
They are fixed together

00:11:28.230 --> 00:11:30.230
This, the nikah was done

00:11:30.230 --> 00:11:32.230
We have a lesson to learn from it

00:11:32.230 --> 00:11:34.230
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala make us those

00:11:34.230 --> 00:11:36.230
Who do not have prolonged engagements

00:11:36.230 --> 00:11:39.230
But rather those who can get the nikah done

00:11:39.230 --> 00:11:40.230
As soon as possible

00:11:40.230 --> 00:11:42.230
And thereafter get together

00:11:42.230 --> 00:11:44.230
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us

00:11:44.230 --> 00:11:45.230
Happiness in our homes

00:11:45.230 --> 00:11:48.230
We also spoke about the first muhajir

00:11:48.230 --> 00:11:50.230
The first person who made hijrah

00:11:50.230 --> 00:11:52.230
For the sake of Allah to Madina Munawwarah

00:11:52.230 --> 00:11:54.230
The story of Abu Salama and Umm Salama

00:11:54.230 --> 00:11:56.230
And Umm Salama, may Allah be pleased with her

00:11:56.230 --> 00:11:58.230
Hind bint, Abu Umayyah

00:11:58.230 --> 00:12:00.230
According to the narrations

00:12:00.230 --> 00:12:01.230
That was her name

00:12:01.230 --> 00:12:03.230
And later on

00:12:03.230 --> 00:12:05.230
She was married to Muhammad SAW

00:12:05.230 --> 00:12:07.230
When her husband passed away

00:12:07.230 --> 00:12:08.230
She endured a lot

00:12:08.230 --> 00:12:09.230
As we mentioned

00:12:09.230 --> 00:12:11.230
She was separated from her husband

00:12:11.230 --> 00:12:13.230
As well as from her little child

00:12:13.230 --> 00:12:14.230
And only after a year

00:12:14.230 --> 00:12:16.230
Or a little bit more than a year

00:12:16.230 --> 00:12:19.230
Did she become united once again with them

00:12:19.230 --> 00:12:22.230
And was she permitted to go back

00:12:22.230 --> 00:12:25.230
Or to go to Madina Munawwarah

00:12:26.230 --> 00:12:28.230
Then we have the first muhajireen

00:12:28.230 --> 00:12:30.230
Also we must make mention of their names

00:12:30.230 --> 00:12:32.230
Mus'ab bint Umayyah r.a

00:12:32.230 --> 00:12:34.230
He had already gone

00:12:34.230 --> 00:12:35.230
After the first akabah

00:12:35.230 --> 00:12:36.230
The first pledge of akabah

00:12:36.230 --> 00:12:38.230
He had gone to Madina Munawwarah

00:12:38.230 --> 00:12:41.230
In order to teach them the deen

00:12:41.230 --> 00:12:43.230
And we said that he had come back

00:12:43.230 --> 00:12:44.230
To Makkah al-Mukarramah

00:12:44.230 --> 00:12:46.230
With the news of the people of Madina

00:12:46.230 --> 00:12:48.230
And so on to Muhammad SAW

00:12:48.230 --> 00:12:50.230
From amongst the early muhajireen

00:12:50.230 --> 00:12:52.230
Abdullah bint Umm Maktoom

00:12:52.230 --> 00:12:54.230
Bilal bint Rabah r.a

00:12:54.230 --> 00:12:57.230
These people went after Muhammad SAW

00:12:57.230 --> 00:12:58.230
Announced to them

00:12:58.230 --> 00:13:01.230
That you can now proceed to Madina Munawwarah

00:13:01.230 --> 00:13:03.230
We are definitely going in that direction

00:13:04.230 --> 00:13:05.230
The question arises

00:13:05.230 --> 00:13:08.230
Why didn't Muhammad SAW lead the way?

00:13:09.230 --> 00:13:10.230
Look at it

00:13:10.230 --> 00:13:12.230
Ironically today

00:13:12.230 --> 00:13:14.230
When there is a country under threat

00:13:14.230 --> 00:13:16.230
Or leaders are in trouble

00:13:16.230 --> 00:13:17.230
They are the first ones who go

00:13:17.230 --> 00:13:19.230
And the people are made to suffer

00:13:19.230 --> 00:13:21.230
They abscond and they run away

00:13:21.230 --> 00:13:23.230
And the people are made to suffer

00:13:23.230 --> 00:13:24.230
With the messenger

00:13:24.230 --> 00:13:25.230
Sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:13:25.230 --> 00:13:27.230
I need to make mention

00:13:27.230 --> 00:13:29.230
It was the other way round

00:13:29.230 --> 00:13:30.230
He made sure everyone went

00:13:30.230 --> 00:13:32.230
He waited for the permission of Allah

00:13:32.230 --> 00:13:34.230
For him to go personally

00:13:34.230 --> 00:13:35.230
So Allah had granted permission

00:13:35.230 --> 00:13:37.230
For the companions to leave

00:13:37.230 --> 00:13:38.230
But not for him

00:13:38.230 --> 00:13:39.230
Subhanallah

00:13:39.230 --> 00:13:40.230
And this is why

00:13:40.230 --> 00:13:42.230
The sahabah r.a

00:13:42.230 --> 00:13:44.230
Make mention of a powerful fact

00:13:44.230 --> 00:13:45.230
Regarding war

00:13:45.230 --> 00:13:47.230
They knew that Muhammad SAW

00:13:47.230 --> 00:13:48.230
Peace be upon him

00:13:48.230 --> 00:13:49.230
Is protected by Allah

00:13:49.230 --> 00:13:50.230
Subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:13:50.230 --> 00:13:52.230
So what they used to say

00:13:57.230 --> 00:13:58.230
Whenever there was a war

00:13:58.230 --> 00:14:00.230
And it became hot

00:14:00.230 --> 00:14:01.230
You know heated

00:14:01.230 --> 00:14:02.230
Very tense

00:14:02.230 --> 00:14:05.230
We all went behind Muhammad SAW

00:14:05.230 --> 00:14:06.230
He was in the front

00:14:06.230 --> 00:14:07.230
Imagine

00:14:07.230 --> 00:14:08.230
This was the messenger

00:14:08.230 --> 00:14:09.230
Because they knew

00:14:09.230 --> 00:14:10.230
We have to be behind him

00:14:10.230 --> 00:14:11.230
We will be protected here

00:14:11.230 --> 00:14:13.230
Today it's the other way round

00:14:13.230 --> 00:14:14.230
The leaders, you don't see them

00:14:14.230 --> 00:14:15.230
They get away

00:14:15.230 --> 00:14:16.230
And thousands

00:14:16.230 --> 00:14:17.230
And hundreds of thousands

00:14:17.230 --> 00:14:18.230
Of their people die

00:14:18.230 --> 00:14:19.230
And are killed

00:14:19.230 --> 00:14:20.230
And they are still having

00:14:20.230 --> 00:14:21.230
A fat life

00:14:21.230 --> 00:14:22.230
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:14:22.230 --> 00:14:23.230
Protect us all

00:14:24.230 --> 00:14:25.230
So Muhammad SAW

00:14:25.230 --> 00:14:27.230
Saw his companions leaving

00:14:27.230 --> 00:14:29.230
From amongst them was Sa'd

00:14:29.230 --> 00:14:31.230
Ibn Abi Waqqas r.a

00:14:31.230 --> 00:14:32.230
Ammar ibn Yasir

00:14:32.230 --> 00:14:35.230
Omar ibn Al-Khattab r.a

00:14:35.230 --> 00:14:37.230
Left with quite a few men

00:14:37.230 --> 00:14:38.230
According to some narration

00:14:38.230 --> 00:14:40.230
He had left with a few people

00:14:40.230 --> 00:14:42.230
And there is a narration

00:14:42.230 --> 00:14:43.230
As we said

00:14:43.230 --> 00:14:44.230
We like to authenticate

00:14:44.230 --> 00:14:45.230
There is a narration that says

00:14:45.230 --> 00:14:48.230
That he stood in Quraish

00:14:48.230 --> 00:14:49.230
And he made an announcement

00:14:49.230 --> 00:14:51.230
In Quraish

00:14:51.230 --> 00:14:52.230
See the rest of the people

00:14:52.230 --> 00:14:53.230
Were going ducking and diving

00:14:53.230 --> 00:14:55.230
Quraish was blocking some of them

00:14:55.230 --> 00:14:56.230
Stealing the wealth of some of them

00:14:56.230 --> 00:14:58.230
Blocking, kidnapping some of them

00:14:58.230 --> 00:15:00.230
And Quraish was hassling them

00:15:00.230 --> 00:15:03.230
It is narrated in one narration

00:15:03.230 --> 00:15:05.230
That Omar ibn Al-Khattab r.a

00:15:05.230 --> 00:15:07.230
Who got up and made an announcement

00:15:07.230 --> 00:15:09.230
Saying that whoever wants

00:15:09.230 --> 00:15:10.230
Their children to be orphaned

00:15:10.230 --> 00:15:13.230
Or their wives to be widowed

00:15:13.230 --> 00:15:15.230
I'll see you in that place there

00:15:15.230 --> 00:15:16.230
In the valley

00:15:16.230 --> 00:15:17.230
Come and try

00:15:17.230 --> 00:15:18.230
See what you want to do

00:15:18.230 --> 00:15:20.230
Look at the words

00:15:20.230 --> 00:15:21.230
However

00:15:21.230 --> 00:15:22.230
That narration

00:15:22.230 --> 00:15:24.230
The chain of it

00:15:24.230 --> 00:15:25.230
For your information

00:15:25.230 --> 00:15:26.230
Is not authentic

00:15:26.230 --> 00:15:27.230
See we make mention of it

00:15:27.230 --> 00:15:29.230
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:15:29.230 --> 00:15:30.230
Grant us goodness

00:15:30.230 --> 00:15:31.230
He was a powerful man

00:15:31.230 --> 00:15:33.230
But there is an authentic narration

00:15:33.230 --> 00:15:34.230
Which is narrated in Sahih Muslim

00:15:34.230 --> 00:15:36.230
And various other books

00:15:36.230 --> 00:15:37.230
That make mention of

00:15:37.230 --> 00:15:39.230
In fact ibn Kathir

00:15:39.230 --> 00:15:40.230
Has made mention of it as well

00:15:40.230 --> 00:15:41.230
In his tafsir

00:15:41.230 --> 00:15:42.230
With an isna

00:15:42.230 --> 00:15:44.230
The chain that is acceptable

00:15:44.230 --> 00:15:46.230
He says Omar ibn Al-Khattab r.a

00:15:46.230 --> 00:15:48.230
When he wanted to make hijrah

00:15:48.230 --> 00:15:49.230
They were persecuting

00:15:49.230 --> 00:15:50.230
The people severely

00:15:50.230 --> 00:15:51.230
The people of Quraish

00:15:51.230 --> 00:15:52.230
Had got together

00:15:52.230 --> 00:15:54.230
And they were persecuting

00:15:54.230 --> 00:15:56.230
In a very systematic way

00:15:56.230 --> 00:15:57.230
Blocking, stopping

00:15:57.230 --> 00:15:58.230
Stealing the wealth off

00:15:58.230 --> 00:16:00.230
And somehow trying to stop them

00:16:00.230 --> 00:16:01.230
And so on

00:16:01.230 --> 00:16:02.230
Kidnapping

00:16:02.230 --> 00:16:04.230
So him and two of his friends

00:16:04.230 --> 00:16:05.230
Which made three of them

00:16:05.230 --> 00:16:08.230
It was Omar ibn Al-Khattab r.a

00:16:08.230 --> 00:16:10.230
Ayyash ibn Abi Rabi'ah

00:16:10.230 --> 00:16:12.230
And Hisham ibn Al-Aas

00:16:12.230 --> 00:16:14.230
These were three people

00:16:14.230 --> 00:16:15.230
They had got together

00:16:15.230 --> 00:16:16.230
And they decided

00:16:16.230 --> 00:16:17.230
Look we're going to collect

00:16:17.230 --> 00:16:18.230
Our provisions

00:16:18.230 --> 00:16:19.230
And we are going to leave

00:16:19.230 --> 00:16:20.230
At a specific time

00:16:20.230 --> 00:16:22.230
Let's meet at that particular time

00:16:22.230 --> 00:16:24.230
At this particular place

00:16:24.230 --> 00:16:26.230
Just on the outskirts of Makkah

00:16:26.230 --> 00:16:27.230
And whoever from amongst us

00:16:27.230 --> 00:16:28.230
Does not come

00:16:28.230 --> 00:16:30.230
It means that that particular person

00:16:30.230 --> 00:16:32.230
Has been held back by Quraish

00:16:32.230 --> 00:16:33.230
The rest of us will carry on

00:16:33.230 --> 00:16:35.230
So at the particular time

00:16:35.230 --> 00:16:37.230
Omar ibn Al-Khattab r.a

00:16:37.230 --> 00:16:38.230
Arrived there

00:16:38.230 --> 00:16:39.230
Ayyash ibn Abi Rabi'ah

00:16:39.230 --> 00:16:40.230
He arrived there as well

00:16:40.230 --> 00:16:42.230
But the third one

00:16:42.230 --> 00:16:44.230
Hisham ibn Al-Aas did not arrive

00:16:44.230 --> 00:16:45.230
When he did not arrive

00:16:45.230 --> 00:16:46.230
The two understood

00:16:46.230 --> 00:16:47.230
That you know what

00:16:47.230 --> 00:16:48.230
We need to make tracks

00:16:48.230 --> 00:16:49.230
And we need to get going

00:16:49.230 --> 00:16:51.230
So the two of them got going

00:16:51.230 --> 00:16:53.230
And they arrived in Madinah Munawarah

00:16:53.230 --> 00:16:54.230
It is reported that

00:16:54.230 --> 00:16:55.230
When they got to Quba

00:16:55.230 --> 00:16:56.230
And that's where

00:16:56.230 --> 00:16:57.230
The base of the Muhajireen

00:16:57.230 --> 00:16:59.230
Had been so far

00:16:59.230 --> 00:17:00.230
The bulk of them

00:17:00.230 --> 00:17:01.230
A lot of them

00:17:01.230 --> 00:17:03.230
Abu Jahl

00:17:03.230 --> 00:17:05.230
And Al-Harith ibn Hisham

00:17:05.230 --> 00:17:06.230
From Quraish

00:17:06.230 --> 00:17:07.230
Had gone all the way

00:17:07.230 --> 00:17:08.230
To Madinah Munawarah

00:17:08.230 --> 00:17:09.230
Imagine

00:17:09.230 --> 00:17:10.230
And this is a correct

00:17:10.230 --> 00:17:11.230
Authentic narration

00:17:11.230 --> 00:17:12.230
They went because

00:17:12.230 --> 00:17:14.230
Ayyash ibn Abi Rabi'ah

00:17:14.230 --> 00:17:15.230
Was a man whom

00:17:15.230 --> 00:17:16.230
They didn't want to lose

00:17:16.230 --> 00:17:18.230
So they spoke to him

00:17:18.230 --> 00:17:19.230
In Quba

00:17:19.230 --> 00:17:21.230
And they had said

00:17:21.230 --> 00:17:22.230
You know what

00:17:22.230 --> 00:17:24.230
Your mother has promised

00:17:24.230 --> 00:17:25.230
That she will not eat

00:17:25.230 --> 00:17:26.230
And she will not do this

00:17:26.230 --> 00:17:27.230
And do that

00:17:27.230 --> 00:17:28.230
Until she sees you

00:17:28.230 --> 00:17:30.230
So you better come back

00:17:30.230 --> 00:17:31.230
So he felt it

00:17:31.230 --> 00:17:32.230
Because he was quite close

00:17:32.230 --> 00:17:33.230
To his mother

00:17:33.230 --> 00:17:35.230
Omar ibn Al-Khattab r.a

00:17:35.230 --> 00:17:36.230
Says they are lying

00:17:36.230 --> 00:17:37.230
They just want to get you

00:17:37.230 --> 00:17:38.230
Kidnap you

00:17:38.230 --> 00:17:39.230
And sort you out

00:17:39.230 --> 00:17:40.230
He says no, no

00:17:40.230 --> 00:17:41.230
My mother

00:17:41.230 --> 00:17:42.230
Omar ibn Al-Khattab r.a

00:17:42.230 --> 00:17:43.230
Says look

00:17:43.230 --> 00:17:44.230
I am telling you

00:17:44.230 --> 00:17:45.230
These people are liars

00:17:45.230 --> 00:17:46.230
They have come

00:17:46.230 --> 00:17:47.230
To block you

00:17:47.230 --> 00:17:48.230
And to disturb you

00:17:48.230 --> 00:17:49.230
And to remove you

00:17:49.230 --> 00:17:50.230
From the deen

00:17:50.230 --> 00:17:51.230
That you have now followed

00:17:51.230 --> 00:17:52.230
So he said no

00:17:52.230 --> 00:17:53.230
Insha'Allah

00:17:53.230 --> 00:17:54.230
I'll go

00:17:54.230 --> 00:17:55.230
I'll sort my things out

00:17:55.230 --> 00:17:56.230
I've got money with someone

00:17:56.230 --> 00:17:57.230
And I will come back

00:17:57.230 --> 00:17:58.230
Very soon

00:17:58.230 --> 00:17:59.230
So Omar ibn Al-Khattab r.a

00:17:59.230 --> 00:18:00.230
Gave him the animal

00:18:00.230 --> 00:18:01.230
And said look

00:18:01.230 --> 00:18:02.230
This animal is faster

00:18:02.230 --> 00:18:03.230
Quicker and better

00:18:03.230 --> 00:18:04.230
Than yours

00:18:04.230 --> 00:18:05.230
Take this and go

00:18:05.230 --> 00:18:06.230
So when he went

00:18:06.230 --> 00:18:07.230
To the road

00:18:07.230 --> 00:18:08.230
And they were at a certain place

00:18:08.230 --> 00:18:09.230
Abu Jahl

00:18:09.230 --> 00:18:10.230
And his friend

00:18:10.230 --> 00:18:11.230
Al-Harith ibn Hisham

00:18:11.230 --> 00:18:12.230
They told him

00:18:12.230 --> 00:18:13.230
Look you know

00:18:13.230 --> 00:18:14.230
Our camel

00:18:14.230 --> 00:18:15.230
There is a problem here

00:18:15.230 --> 00:18:16.230
With it

00:18:16.230 --> 00:18:17.230
So why don't you stop

00:18:17.230 --> 00:18:18.230
And let me ride on yours

00:18:18.230 --> 00:18:19.230
When he stopped

00:18:19.230 --> 00:18:20.230
Got down

00:18:20.230 --> 00:18:21.230
They kidnapped him

00:18:21.230 --> 00:18:22.230
Tied him

00:18:22.230 --> 00:18:23.230
Put him onto the back

00:18:23.230 --> 00:18:24.230
Of the camel

00:18:24.230 --> 00:18:25.230
Took him to Makkah al-Mukarramah

00:18:25.230 --> 00:18:26.230
And they kept him

00:18:26.230 --> 00:18:27.230
In that particular place

00:18:27.230 --> 00:18:28.230
They suffocated him

00:18:28.230 --> 00:18:29.230
At the same time

00:18:29.230 --> 00:18:30.230
They punished him

00:18:30.230 --> 00:18:31.230
Penalized him

00:18:31.230 --> 00:18:33.230
Until news got around

00:18:33.230 --> 00:18:34.230
That this man has left

00:18:34.230 --> 00:18:35.230
His faith

00:18:35.230 --> 00:18:36.230
News went to

00:18:36.230 --> 00:18:37.230
Madinah Munawwara

00:18:37.230 --> 00:18:38.230
That this man has now

00:18:38.230 --> 00:18:40.230
Returned to the religion of

00:18:40.230 --> 00:18:42.230
The forefathers

00:18:42.230 --> 00:18:43.230
Shirk and polytheism

00:18:43.230 --> 00:18:44.230
And so on

00:18:44.230 --> 00:18:45.230
And the same news

00:18:45.230 --> 00:18:46.230
Arrived about

00:18:46.230 --> 00:18:47.230
The third person

00:18:47.230 --> 00:18:48.230
Who was supposed to have

00:18:48.230 --> 00:18:49.230
Joined Umar ibn al-Khattab

00:18:49.230 --> 00:18:51.230
And Ayyash ibn Abi Rabi'a

00:18:51.230 --> 00:18:52.230
And his name was

00:18:52.230 --> 00:18:54.230
Hisham ibn al-'As

00:18:54.230 --> 00:18:55.230
So news had got to them

00:18:55.230 --> 00:18:56.230
That these two

00:18:56.230 --> 00:18:58.230
Had reneged from Islam

00:18:58.230 --> 00:19:00.230
And turned away

00:19:00.230 --> 00:19:01.230
Later on

00:19:01.230 --> 00:19:02.230
When Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:19:02.230 --> 00:19:03.230
Had come

00:19:03.230 --> 00:19:04.230
Verses were revealed

00:19:04.230 --> 00:19:06.230
Qul ya ibaadiya

00:19:06.230 --> 00:19:08.230
Allatheena asrafoo

00:19:08.230 --> 00:19:11.230
Ala anfusihim

00:19:11.230 --> 00:19:13.230
La taqnatoo

00:19:13.230 --> 00:19:15.230
Min rahmatillah

00:19:15.230 --> 00:19:17.230
Inna Allah

00:19:17.230 --> 00:19:19.230
Yaghfiru al-dhunub

00:19:19.230 --> 00:19:20.230
Jami'a

00:19:20.230 --> 00:19:23.230
Inna huwa al-ghfuru

00:19:23.230 --> 00:19:24.230
Al-rahim

00:19:24.230 --> 00:19:26.230
Wa aneebu

00:19:26.230 --> 00:19:28.230
Ila rabbikum

00:19:28.230 --> 00:19:32.230
Wa aslimu lahu min qabli

00:19:32.230 --> 00:19:35.230
An ya'tiyakumu al-'alabu

00:19:35.230 --> 00:19:40.230
Thumma la tunsaron

00:19:40.230 --> 00:19:43.230
Say, O Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:19:43.230 --> 00:19:45.230
All my worshipers

00:19:45.230 --> 00:19:46.230
Meaning all worshipers

00:19:46.230 --> 00:19:48.230
Of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:19:48.230 --> 00:19:49.230
Who have transgressed

00:19:49.230 --> 00:19:51.230
Against themselves

00:19:51.230 --> 00:19:53.230
Never lose hope

00:19:53.230 --> 00:19:54.230
In the mercy of Allah

00:19:54.230 --> 00:19:55.230
Subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:19:55.230 --> 00:19:56.230
For indeed

00:19:56.230 --> 00:19:58.230
He forgives all sins

00:19:58.230 --> 00:19:59.230
He is most forgiving

00:19:59.230 --> 00:20:01.230
Most merciful

00:20:01.230 --> 00:20:04.230
Turn to him before it is too late

00:20:04.230 --> 00:20:06.230
Before a day comes to you of punishment

00:20:06.230 --> 00:20:08.230
And then you will not be helped

00:20:08.230 --> 00:20:10.230
So Umar ibn Al-Khattab radiallahu anhu

00:20:10.230 --> 00:20:11.230
Wrote these verses

00:20:11.230 --> 00:20:14.230
And sent them to his two friends

00:20:14.230 --> 00:20:15.230
Hisham ibn Al-Aas

00:20:15.230 --> 00:20:17.230
And Ayyash ibn Abi Rabi'ah

00:20:17.230 --> 00:20:19.230
And Hisham makes mention of how

00:20:19.230 --> 00:20:20.230
When he read it

00:20:20.230 --> 00:20:23.230
He knew that this is revealed because of me

00:20:23.230 --> 00:20:25.230
He was pacing by the Tua

00:20:25.230 --> 00:20:26.230
A name of a place close to

00:20:26.230 --> 00:20:28.230
Makkat al-Mukarrama

00:20:28.230 --> 00:20:30.230
And he was pacing up and down

00:20:30.230 --> 00:20:32.230
And he knew this was for him

00:20:32.230 --> 00:20:33.230
And after some time

00:20:33.230 --> 00:20:34.230
They had been released

00:20:34.230 --> 00:20:37.230
And they went to Medina al-Munawwara

00:20:37.230 --> 00:20:39.230
At a certain stage

00:20:39.230 --> 00:20:41.230
So this was also part of the suffering

00:20:41.230 --> 00:20:43.230
Of some of those who had intended

00:20:43.230 --> 00:20:45.230
To engage in Hijra

00:20:45.230 --> 00:20:47.230
There was one who engaged also

00:20:47.230 --> 00:20:49.230
Whom we need to mention his name

00:20:49.230 --> 00:20:51.230
Hamza ibn Abdul Muttalib

00:20:51.230 --> 00:20:53.230
Remember the powerful man

00:20:53.230 --> 00:20:54.230
The powerful man

00:20:54.230 --> 00:20:56.230
The uncle of Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:20:56.230 --> 00:20:58.230
Believe me they all made Hijra

00:20:58.230 --> 00:21:00.230
Instructed by Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:21:00.230 --> 00:21:02.230
To leave and the bulk of them left

00:21:02.230 --> 00:21:04.230
Makkah started becoming quiet

00:21:04.230 --> 00:21:06.230
It started becoming quiet

00:21:06.230 --> 00:21:08.230
And the Mushriks became very eerie

00:21:08.230 --> 00:21:10.230
As we will see in a few moments

00:21:10.230 --> 00:21:12.230
But there was one man who wanted to make Hijra

00:21:12.230 --> 00:21:14.230
And the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:21:14.230 --> 00:21:15.230
Stopped him

00:21:15.230 --> 00:21:16.230
Who was that?

00:21:16.230 --> 00:21:18.230
Abu Bakr al-Siddiq radiallahu anhu

00:21:18.230 --> 00:21:20.230
The Prophet sallallahu alayhi wasallam says

00:21:20.230 --> 00:21:22.230
Don't make haste

00:21:22.230 --> 00:21:24.230
Oh Abu Bakr

00:21:24.230 --> 00:21:25.230
Don't make haste

00:21:25.230 --> 00:21:26.230
Oh Abu Bakr

00:21:26.230 --> 00:21:28.230
In going for the Hijra

00:21:28.230 --> 00:21:30.230
And Abu Bakr radiallahu anhu

00:21:30.230 --> 00:21:32.230
Understood that this means

00:21:32.230 --> 00:21:34.230
Perhaps he would then go with

00:21:34.230 --> 00:21:36.230
Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:21:36.230 --> 00:21:37.230
The day he left

00:21:37.230 --> 00:21:39.230
Also Ali ibn Abi Talib radiallahu anhu

00:21:39.230 --> 00:21:41.230
Who was much younger than them

00:21:41.230 --> 00:21:43.230
Was also from amongst those who were instructed to stay

00:21:43.230 --> 00:21:45.230
And the reasons were many

00:21:45.230 --> 00:21:46.230
One of them was

00:21:46.230 --> 00:21:48.230
Revelation from Allah sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:21:48.230 --> 00:21:50.230
Another was

00:21:50.230 --> 00:21:53.230
That Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:21:53.230 --> 00:21:55.230
He had a strange relation

00:21:55.230 --> 00:21:57.230
With the Mushriks of Quraysh

00:21:57.230 --> 00:21:58.230
In that

00:21:58.230 --> 00:22:00.230
They didn't agree with his message

00:22:00.230 --> 00:22:02.230
But they trusted him the most

00:22:02.230 --> 00:22:04.230
All of them who had anything valuable

00:22:04.230 --> 00:22:06.230
Who wanted it for safe keeping

00:22:06.230 --> 00:22:08.230
Went to Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:22:08.230 --> 00:22:10.230
Even though they were at loggerheads with him

00:22:10.230 --> 00:22:11.230
And they used to say

00:22:11.230 --> 00:22:12.230
You know you're a trustworthy man

00:22:12.230 --> 00:22:14.230
Just keep this

00:22:14.230 --> 00:22:15.230
How many of us

00:22:15.230 --> 00:22:17.230
Even enemy had to come to us

00:22:17.230 --> 00:22:19.230
And we had some of his wealth

00:22:19.230 --> 00:22:20.230
Oh he came and said

00:22:20.230 --> 00:22:21.230
You know what

00:22:21.230 --> 00:22:22.230
I just want to entrust you with this

00:22:22.230 --> 00:22:23.230
One million rands

00:22:23.230 --> 00:22:24.230
Just hold it for me

00:22:24.230 --> 00:22:25.230
What would happen

00:22:25.230 --> 00:22:27.230
I think before we know it

00:22:27.230 --> 00:22:28.230
As we're counting it

00:22:28.230 --> 00:22:29.230
It will become nine hundred thousand

00:22:29.230 --> 00:22:30.230
Allah protect us

00:22:30.230 --> 00:22:31.230
And we count it again

00:22:31.230 --> 00:22:32.230
It becomes eight hundred thousand

00:22:32.230 --> 00:22:33.230
That's the famous one

00:22:33.230 --> 00:22:34.230
Mashallah

00:22:34.230 --> 00:22:36.230
May Allah sallallahu alayhi wasallam protect us

00:22:36.230 --> 00:22:38.230
Look at Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:22:38.230 --> 00:22:40.230
What an honest upright man

00:22:40.230 --> 00:22:41.230
That even his own enemies

00:22:41.230 --> 00:22:44.230
Bore witness that he was honest

00:22:44.230 --> 00:22:45.230
And this is why he said to them

00:22:45.230 --> 00:22:47.230
Oh my people

00:22:47.230 --> 00:22:49.230
Do you think I would lie to you

00:22:49.230 --> 00:22:50.230
If I were to lie

00:22:50.230 --> 00:22:51.230
I wouldn't ever lie about

00:22:51.230 --> 00:22:53.230
What I'm just telling you now

00:22:53.230 --> 00:22:54.230
Subhanallah

00:22:54.230 --> 00:22:56.230
May Allah sallallahu alayhi wasallam protect us all

00:22:56.230 --> 00:22:57.230
And grant us goodness

00:22:57.230 --> 00:22:59.230
So Ali radiallahu anhu as well

00:22:59.230 --> 00:23:00.230
He had stayed behind

00:23:00.230 --> 00:23:03.230
Now the mushriks of Quraish

00:23:03.230 --> 00:23:05.230
As I said they became very wary

00:23:05.230 --> 00:23:06.230
Of the situation

00:23:06.230 --> 00:23:08.230
And they were pacing up and down

00:23:08.230 --> 00:23:10.230
They were very very unsettled

00:23:10.230 --> 00:23:13.230
Because they were faced with a problem

00:23:13.230 --> 00:23:14.230
What was the problem

00:23:14.230 --> 00:23:16.230
They had a meeting in a place

00:23:16.230 --> 00:23:18.230
Known as Darul Nadwa

00:23:18.230 --> 00:23:19.230
Darul Nadwa was this place

00:23:19.230 --> 00:23:21.230
Where all their planning

00:23:21.230 --> 00:23:22.230
And plotting used to happen

00:23:22.230 --> 00:23:25.230
Quraish, whatever big decisions

00:23:25.230 --> 00:23:26.230
They wanted to arrive at

00:23:26.230 --> 00:23:28.230
Were all made in Darul Nadwa

00:23:28.230 --> 00:23:31.230
It was the house of Qusay Ibn-ul-Kilal

00:23:31.230 --> 00:23:34.230
He was one of the members of Quraish

00:23:34.230 --> 00:23:35.230
And at his house

00:23:35.230 --> 00:23:36.230
They called it Darul Nadwa

00:23:36.230 --> 00:23:39.230
They got together in order to decide

00:23:39.230 --> 00:23:42.230
What should we do with this Muhammad Ibn Abdullah

00:23:42.230 --> 00:23:44.230
Sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:23:44.230 --> 00:23:47.230
So some of them said

00:23:47.230 --> 00:23:49.230
Let us confine him

00:23:49.230 --> 00:23:51.230
Let us confine him

00:23:51.230 --> 00:23:53.230
And keep him, kidnap him

00:23:53.230 --> 00:23:55.230
And seal him completely

00:23:55.230 --> 00:23:56.230
So no one can come

00:23:56.230 --> 00:23:57.230
And no one can go

00:23:57.230 --> 00:23:59.230
And no one will know where he is

00:23:59.230 --> 00:24:01.230
That was one plan

00:24:01.230 --> 00:24:02.230
The next plan they said

00:24:02.230 --> 00:24:04.230
Others said no no no

00:24:04.230 --> 00:24:05.230
We cannot do that

00:24:05.230 --> 00:24:07.230
The reason is if we confine him

00:24:07.230 --> 00:24:09.230
Now he has followers in Yathrib

00:24:09.230 --> 00:24:11.230
Which is Madinah Munawwara

00:24:11.230 --> 00:24:13.230
And most of his companions are there

00:24:13.230 --> 00:24:15.230
They will prepare an army

00:24:15.230 --> 00:24:17.230
And come to release him from kidnap

00:24:17.230 --> 00:24:19.230
So there's no point in kidnapping him

00:24:19.230 --> 00:24:21.230
Now that plan also failed

00:24:21.230 --> 00:24:22.230
From themselves

00:24:22.230 --> 00:24:23.230
They disagreed with it

00:24:23.230 --> 00:24:25.230
After that they said okay

00:24:25.230 --> 00:24:26.230
Let's kick him out

00:24:26.230 --> 00:24:28.230
Let's boot him out of this place

00:24:28.230 --> 00:24:30.230
No problem, allow him to leave

00:24:30.230 --> 00:24:31.230
And the other said

00:24:31.230 --> 00:24:32.230
How can you let him leave?

00:24:32.230 --> 00:24:33.230
If he leaves

00:24:33.230 --> 00:24:35.230
He's going to go to Madinah Munawwara

00:24:35.230 --> 00:24:36.230
He's going to become powerful

00:24:36.230 --> 00:24:38.230
People who listen to his words

00:24:38.230 --> 00:24:39.230
Are all accepting

00:24:39.230 --> 00:24:41.230
Everybody is accepting

00:24:41.230 --> 00:24:43.230
And the numbers are only growing

00:24:43.230 --> 00:24:44.230
They are not diminishing

00:24:44.230 --> 00:24:46.230
So they will prepare an army

00:24:46.230 --> 00:24:47.230
In a short time

00:24:47.230 --> 00:24:49.230
And they will come to attack us

00:24:49.230 --> 00:24:50.230
How can we let him go?

00:24:50.230 --> 00:24:51.230
So they said no

00:24:51.230 --> 00:24:52.230
Don't let him go

00:24:52.230 --> 00:24:54.230
Okay, that's plan B

00:24:54.230 --> 00:24:55.230
It failed itself

00:24:55.230 --> 00:24:57.230
Because they found fault in it

00:24:57.230 --> 00:24:58.230
Plan C

00:24:58.230 --> 00:25:00.230
Let us just kill him

00:25:00.230 --> 00:25:01.230
Now if we kill him

00:25:01.230 --> 00:25:02.230
His followers will come

00:25:02.230 --> 00:25:05.230
And they will still come and attack us

00:25:05.230 --> 00:25:07.230
But this perhaps might be a good idea

00:25:07.230 --> 00:25:09.230
If we think of how to do it

00:25:09.230 --> 00:25:10.230
So how did they want to do it?

00:25:10.230 --> 00:25:11.230
They said look

00:25:11.230 --> 00:25:13.230
This Quraysh is made up of so many

00:25:13.230 --> 00:25:14.230
Different tribes

00:25:14.230 --> 00:25:15.230
Different little clans

00:25:15.230 --> 00:25:16.230
So we have Banu Hashim

00:25:16.230 --> 00:25:17.230
Banu this, Banu that

00:25:17.230 --> 00:25:19.230
Banu Abdi Manaf and so on

00:25:19.230 --> 00:25:20.230
He is from Banu Abdi Manaf

00:25:20.230 --> 00:25:21.230
If we were to kill him

00:25:21.230 --> 00:25:24.230
Banu Abdi Manaf can come

00:25:24.230 --> 00:25:26.230
And wage war against the killers

00:25:26.230 --> 00:25:28.230
But if there are so many killers

00:25:28.230 --> 00:25:29.230
One from every tribe

00:25:29.230 --> 00:25:31.230
Then this Banu Abdi Manaf

00:25:31.230 --> 00:25:33.230
Will never be able to come out

00:25:33.230 --> 00:25:34.230
And fight everyone

00:25:34.230 --> 00:25:36.230
They can't fight the whole of Quraysh

00:25:36.230 --> 00:25:38.230
So what happened is

00:25:38.230 --> 00:25:39.230
Subhanallah, they decided

00:25:39.230 --> 00:25:42.230
Okay, what we do is tomorrow

00:25:42.230 --> 00:25:44.230
Tonight we will send one strong man

00:25:44.230 --> 00:25:47.230
From every single clan of ours

00:25:47.230 --> 00:25:49.230
And we'll encircle his home

00:25:49.230 --> 00:25:51.230
And then what will happen is

00:25:51.230 --> 00:25:53.230
As he emerges from his house

00:25:53.230 --> 00:25:54.230
In the morning

00:25:54.230 --> 00:25:56.230
We whack him altogether

00:25:56.230 --> 00:25:57.230
And who will be to blame?

00:25:57.230 --> 00:25:58.230
The whole lot

00:25:58.230 --> 00:26:00.230
So one from every single tribe

00:26:00.230 --> 00:26:01.230
And Banu Abdi Manaf

00:26:01.230 --> 00:26:03.230
Will not be able to avenge or retaliate

00:26:03.230 --> 00:26:04.230
They will have to accept

00:26:04.230 --> 00:26:05.230
Some blood money

00:26:05.230 --> 00:26:07.230
And the blood money will be very little

00:26:07.230 --> 00:26:08.230
Because we are going to divide it

00:26:08.230 --> 00:26:10.230
Amongst all of us here

00:26:10.230 --> 00:26:11.230
So that's how they planned to kill him

00:26:12.230 --> 00:26:14.230
Sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:26:14.230 --> 00:26:16.230
Allah informed him of everything

00:26:16.230 --> 00:26:18.230
He knew what was exactly planned

00:26:18.230 --> 00:26:19.230
And you see the time when

00:26:19.230 --> 00:26:22.230
He told Abu Bakr as-Siddiq radiallahu anhu

00:26:22.230 --> 00:26:23.230
Not to make haste

00:26:23.230 --> 00:26:24.230
At that time

00:26:24.230 --> 00:26:26.230
Abu Bakr was very intelligent

00:26:26.230 --> 00:26:28.230
He immediately purchased two camels

00:26:28.230 --> 00:26:31.230
And he made sure he fed them well

00:26:31.230 --> 00:26:32.230
So that they would be strong

00:26:32.230 --> 00:26:33.230
For a long journey

00:26:33.230 --> 00:26:35.230
Look at the intelligence of the man

00:26:35.230 --> 00:26:36.230
Subhanallah

00:26:36.230 --> 00:26:38.230
He started preparing for the journey

00:26:38.230 --> 00:26:40.230
This was before all this

00:26:40.230 --> 00:26:41.230
When the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:26:41.230 --> 00:26:42.230
Had told him

00:26:42.230 --> 00:26:43.230
Don't make haste

00:26:43.230 --> 00:26:44.230
He understood

00:26:44.230 --> 00:26:45.230
He already purchased the animals

00:26:45.230 --> 00:26:46.230
And started preparing it

00:26:46.230 --> 00:26:47.230
Now on that day

00:26:47.230 --> 00:26:48.230
Suddenly

00:26:48.230 --> 00:26:51.230
The Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:26:51.230 --> 00:26:54.230
Who does not normally come out

00:26:54.230 --> 00:26:55.230
During the daylight

00:26:55.230 --> 00:26:56.230
To visit people

00:26:56.230 --> 00:26:59.230
He visited Abu Bakr as-Siddiq radiallahu anhu

00:26:59.230 --> 00:27:00.230
In his home

00:27:00.230 --> 00:27:02.230
In the heat of the afternoon

00:27:02.230 --> 00:27:03.230
The heat of the afternoon

00:27:03.230 --> 00:27:05.230
And he was covered

00:27:05.230 --> 00:27:06.230
And he was walking quick

00:27:06.230 --> 00:27:07.230
He knocked on the door

00:27:07.230 --> 00:27:08.230
It opened

00:27:08.230 --> 00:27:10.230
Oh, it's Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:27:10.230 --> 00:27:11.230
Aisha radiallahu anhu says

00:27:11.230 --> 00:27:13.230
We saw him come in

00:27:13.230 --> 00:27:14.230
And when he came in

00:27:14.230 --> 00:27:15.230
Obviously this was his wife

00:27:15.230 --> 00:27:18.230
But they had not yet lived together

00:27:18.230 --> 00:27:19.230
The Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:27:19.230 --> 00:27:22.230
Asked for Abu Bakr as-Siddiq radiallahu anhu

00:27:22.230 --> 00:27:23.230
Welcomed him and sat down

00:27:23.230 --> 00:27:26.230
And the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam says

00:27:26.230 --> 00:27:27.230
Whoever is in this home

00:27:27.230 --> 00:27:28.230
Tell them to leave

00:27:28.230 --> 00:27:31.230
Because there was something important to discuss

00:27:31.230 --> 00:27:33.230
So Abu Bakr as-Siddiq radiallahu anhu says

00:27:33.230 --> 00:27:36.230
There are none other than my own family

00:27:36.230 --> 00:27:37.230
My own daughters

00:27:37.230 --> 00:27:38.230
No one else

00:27:38.230 --> 00:27:40.230
So then he spoke immediately

00:27:40.230 --> 00:27:41.230
Few words

00:27:41.230 --> 00:27:42.230
He says look

00:27:42.230 --> 00:27:45.230
Allah has given me permission to leave

00:27:45.230 --> 00:27:46.230
Subhanallah

00:27:46.230 --> 00:27:47.230
So this was what they were waiting for

00:27:47.230 --> 00:27:49.230
Permission to leave

00:27:49.230 --> 00:27:50.230
Without permission

00:27:50.230 --> 00:27:52.230
They were not allowed to leave

00:27:52.230 --> 00:27:53.230
Now this was in the month of Safar

00:27:53.230 --> 00:27:55.230
Towards the end of Safar

00:27:55.230 --> 00:27:57.230
It is reported the 27th of Safar

00:27:57.230 --> 00:27:59.230
Somewhere near the end of Safar

00:27:59.230 --> 00:28:01.230
And Allah had instructed me to leave

00:28:01.230 --> 00:28:03.230
Most of the companions had already gone

00:28:03.230 --> 00:28:05.230
So what I need you to do

00:28:05.230 --> 00:28:07.230
Abu Bakr is the following

00:28:07.230 --> 00:28:10.230
We will meet at this particular cave

00:28:10.230 --> 00:28:12.230
We will meet at a specific place

00:28:12.230 --> 00:28:14.230
And that is where the two of us will get together

00:28:14.230 --> 00:28:15.230
Or better still

00:28:15.230 --> 00:28:17.230
According to some narrations

00:28:17.230 --> 00:28:19.230
I will come to you by night

00:28:19.230 --> 00:28:21.230
And the two of us will get together

00:28:21.230 --> 00:28:22.230
And we will leave

00:28:22.230 --> 00:28:23.230
We will go to a cave

00:28:23.230 --> 00:28:25.230
And spend some time in the cave

00:28:25.230 --> 00:28:26.230
Right on the outskirts of Makkah

00:28:26.230 --> 00:28:28.230
Because as soon as Quraysh knows

00:28:28.230 --> 00:28:29.230
That we have left

00:28:29.230 --> 00:28:31.230
They are going to send little armies

00:28:31.230 --> 00:28:32.230
And little groups of people

00:28:32.230 --> 00:28:34.230
All around to go in various directions

00:28:34.230 --> 00:28:35.230
To look for us

00:28:35.230 --> 00:28:37.230
If we are on the road at the time

00:28:37.230 --> 00:28:38.230
They are going to catch us

00:28:38.230 --> 00:28:40.230
And if we are somewhere

00:28:40.230 --> 00:28:41.230
Where they cannot see

00:28:41.230 --> 00:28:43.230
Then they will not be able to catch us at all

00:28:43.230 --> 00:28:45.230
And they won't even find out

00:28:45.230 --> 00:28:46.230
They will give up hope

00:28:46.230 --> 00:28:48.230
So we will wait there

00:28:48.230 --> 00:28:51.230
And then they had a guide whom they needed

00:28:51.230 --> 00:28:53.230
Because the road it was difficult

00:28:53.230 --> 00:28:54.230
As I told you yesterday

00:28:54.230 --> 00:28:56.230
People needed a guide

00:28:56.230 --> 00:28:58.230
Those who were not very used to the road

00:28:58.230 --> 00:28:59.230
Would have needed a guide

00:28:59.230 --> 00:29:00.230
So Subhanallah

00:29:00.230 --> 00:29:02.230
Abdullah ibn Uraqiq

00:29:02.230 --> 00:29:03.230
He was a man who was a Mushrik

00:29:03.230 --> 00:29:06.230
But he was an honest upright guide

00:29:06.230 --> 00:29:08.230
And he was a person whom they had trusted

00:29:08.230 --> 00:29:10.230
So they hired him

00:29:10.230 --> 00:29:11.230
Sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:29:11.230 --> 00:29:12.230
Hired him

00:29:12.230 --> 00:29:14.230
And told him the following

00:29:14.230 --> 00:29:17.230
Look we want you to meet us

00:29:17.230 --> 00:29:19.230
At this cave in three days time

00:29:19.230 --> 00:29:20.230
That's it

00:29:20.230 --> 00:29:21.230
Subhanallah

00:29:21.230 --> 00:29:22.230
So he didn't know too many details

00:29:22.230 --> 00:29:23.230
All he knew is

00:29:23.230 --> 00:29:24.230
I will meet these people

00:29:24.230 --> 00:29:25.230
At this cave three days time

00:29:25.230 --> 00:29:27.230
And here are the two camels

00:29:27.230 --> 00:29:28.230
Take them with you

00:29:28.230 --> 00:29:30.230
And you bring them when you come

00:29:30.230 --> 00:29:32.230
So he took the camels

00:29:32.230 --> 00:29:35.230
So in the meantime

00:29:35.230 --> 00:29:37.230
Ali radiallahu anhu

00:29:37.230 --> 00:29:39.230
Was instructed by Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:29:39.230 --> 00:29:40.230
Look tonight

00:29:40.230 --> 00:29:42.230
You will sleep in my bedding

00:29:42.230 --> 00:29:44.230
Here in my home

00:29:44.230 --> 00:29:46.230
And in the morning

00:29:46.230 --> 00:29:47.230
You will get up as usual

00:29:47.230 --> 00:29:52.230
And I have so many items of value

00:29:52.230 --> 00:29:53.230
Which belong to Quraysh

00:29:53.230 --> 00:29:55.230
That they have kept with me

00:29:55.230 --> 00:29:57.230
And everything is properly recorded

00:29:57.230 --> 00:29:59.230
You need to take all these things

00:29:59.230 --> 00:30:00.230
And give them back to them

00:30:00.230 --> 00:30:01.230
And give them back to them

00:30:01.230 --> 00:30:02.230
So ever they belong to

00:30:02.230 --> 00:30:05.230
So that nothing is left in my home

00:30:05.230 --> 00:30:06.230
That belongs to someone else

00:30:06.230 --> 00:30:08.230
So that was one of the reasons

00:30:08.230 --> 00:30:11.230
Why he was kept there as well

00:30:11.230 --> 00:30:13.230
Because if Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:30:13.230 --> 00:30:15.230
Had gone to give back Quraysh their things

00:30:15.230 --> 00:30:16.230
They would have blocked him

00:30:16.230 --> 00:30:18.230
They would have known he's leaving

00:30:18.230 --> 00:30:21.230
So the fact that he still had the items

00:30:21.230 --> 00:30:22.230
Some of Quraysh doubted

00:30:22.230 --> 00:30:24.230
Thinking that this man couldn't have gone

00:30:24.230 --> 00:30:25.230
With all our things

00:30:25.230 --> 00:30:26.230
He is very trustworthy

00:30:26.230 --> 00:30:27.230
See

00:30:27.230 --> 00:30:28.230
So this was also part of the plan

00:30:28.230 --> 00:30:30.230
Of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:30:30.230 --> 00:30:31.230
In the meantime

00:30:31.230 --> 00:30:34.230
The daughter of Abu Bakr al-Siddiq radiallahu anhu

00:30:34.230 --> 00:30:36.230
Asma binti Abi Bakr

00:30:36.230 --> 00:30:39.230
She had made up with her belt

00:30:39.230 --> 00:30:41.230
Two little holding

00:30:41.230 --> 00:30:43.230
Meaning food holders

00:30:43.230 --> 00:30:44.230
And she had

00:30:44.230 --> 00:30:47.230
She used to take the food to that cave

00:30:47.230 --> 00:30:48.230
When they got to the cave inshallah

00:30:48.230 --> 00:30:49.230
We will still get to that

00:30:49.230 --> 00:30:51.230
But she was the one who brought the food

00:30:51.230 --> 00:30:53.230
Up and down from the cave

00:30:53.230 --> 00:30:56.230
To the cave from the home

00:30:56.230 --> 00:30:59.230
Now that evening the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:30:59.230 --> 00:31:00.230
Was in his home

00:31:00.230 --> 00:31:02.230
And as per the plan of Quraysh

00:31:02.230 --> 00:31:05.230
These men had come and encircled the house

00:31:05.230 --> 00:31:07.230
Ali radiallahu anhu was in with him

00:31:07.230 --> 00:31:08.230
Subhanallah

00:31:08.230 --> 00:31:10.230
And they knew the man is inside

00:31:10.230 --> 00:31:11.230
They were happy

00:31:11.230 --> 00:31:14.230
So as night fell

00:31:14.230 --> 00:31:15.230
Some of them were tired

00:31:15.230 --> 00:31:17.230
And some of them were this and that

00:31:17.230 --> 00:31:19.230
And they were not really concentrating

00:31:19.230 --> 00:31:20.230
The Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:31:20.230 --> 00:31:23.230
Was instructed by Allah to leave the home

00:31:23.230 --> 00:31:24.230
When he left the home

00:31:24.230 --> 00:31:25.230
According to one of the narrations

00:31:25.230 --> 00:31:27.230
He was reading verses of surat Yasin

00:31:27.230 --> 00:31:31.230
وَجَعَلْنَا مِن بَيْنِ أَيْدِهِمْ سَدًا وَمِنْ خَلْفِهِمْ سَدًا

00:31:31.230 --> 00:31:33.230
فَأَغْشَيْنَاهُمْ فَهُمْ لَا يُبْصِرُونَ

00:31:33.230 --> 00:31:36.230
He took a small little hand of dust

00:31:36.230 --> 00:31:38.230
And he just threw it

00:31:38.230 --> 00:31:41.230
Just as into the air

00:31:41.230 --> 00:31:43.230
And by the will of Allah

00:31:43.230 --> 00:31:45.230
Subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:31:45.230 --> 00:31:48.230
Every one of those young men

00:31:48.230 --> 00:31:51.230
Who were waiting to snap at him

00:31:51.230 --> 00:31:53.230
Happened to have some grit

00:31:53.230 --> 00:31:56.230
In their eyes from the dust he threw

00:31:56.230 --> 00:31:59.230
Now the meaning of the verse of surah Yasin

00:31:59.230 --> 00:32:02.230
And we have placed a bar before them

00:32:02.230 --> 00:32:04.230
And a bar behind them

00:32:04.230 --> 00:32:05.230
And we have covered them

00:32:05.230 --> 00:32:07.230
So that they cannot see

00:32:07.230 --> 00:32:09.230
That's the meaning of the verse

00:32:09.230 --> 00:32:10.230
So as he read the verse

00:32:10.230 --> 00:32:13.230
And he threw this little handful of dust

00:32:13.230 --> 00:32:15.230
They all at one time

00:32:15.230 --> 00:32:17.230
Began to rub their eyes

00:32:17.230 --> 00:32:18.230
Now you tell me

00:32:18.230 --> 00:32:20.230
If you were rubbing your eyes now

00:32:20.230 --> 00:32:21.230
How would you know

00:32:21.230 --> 00:32:23.230
You know who else is rubbing their eyes

00:32:23.230 --> 00:32:24.230
You wouldn't know

00:32:24.230 --> 00:32:26.230
So all of them at the same time

00:32:26.230 --> 00:32:28.230
Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم stepped out

00:32:28.230 --> 00:32:29.230
And he was gone

00:32:29.230 --> 00:32:32.230
Out to Abu Bakr الصديق رضي الله عنه's home

00:32:32.230 --> 00:32:34.230
And the two of them left for the cave

00:32:34.230 --> 00:32:36.230
In no time they were in that cave

00:32:36.230 --> 00:32:37.230
Abu Bakr الصديق رضي الله عنه

00:32:37.230 --> 00:32:39.230
Went in first in order to look

00:32:39.230 --> 00:32:41.230
It was at the top of Mount Thawr

00:32:41.230 --> 00:32:42.230
Mount Thawr

00:32:42.230 --> 00:32:43.230
I'm sure those who visited Makkah

00:32:43.230 --> 00:32:45.230
Have been shown just on the outskirts of

00:32:45.230 --> 00:32:47.230
Makkah المكرمة

00:32:47.230 --> 00:32:50.230
And when Abu Bakr الصديق رضي الله عنه

00:32:50.230 --> 00:32:52.230
Went in to see that there is no snake

00:32:52.230 --> 00:32:53.230
Or nothing harmful inside

00:32:53.230 --> 00:32:55.230
Thereafter Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:32:55.230 --> 00:32:57.230
Went in and the two of them

00:32:57.230 --> 00:32:58.230
Camped there

00:32:58.230 --> 00:32:59.230
They waited there

00:32:59.230 --> 00:33:00.230
In the meantime

00:33:00.230 --> 00:33:02.230
It's important to know what happened there

00:33:02.230 --> 00:33:03.230
Back at home

00:33:03.230 --> 00:33:04.230
Ali رضي الله عنه

00:33:04.230 --> 00:33:06.230
Was covered with the clothing of

00:33:06.230 --> 00:33:08.230
Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:33:08.230 --> 00:33:10.230
And when he got up

00:33:10.230 --> 00:33:13.230
And the narrations make mention of

00:33:13.230 --> 00:33:15.230
How when he stepped out

00:33:15.230 --> 00:33:16.230
They were so excited

00:33:16.230 --> 00:33:18.230
Until they found out

00:33:18.230 --> 00:33:19.230
This is Ali

00:33:19.230 --> 00:33:20.230
Ibn Abi Talib

00:33:20.230 --> 00:33:21.230
So where is the man?

00:33:21.230 --> 00:33:22.230
The man is not here

00:33:22.230 --> 00:33:23.230
Where is he?

00:33:23.230 --> 00:33:24.230
I don't know

00:33:24.230 --> 00:33:26.230
Perhaps he's gone somewhere

00:33:26.230 --> 00:33:28.230
But how could this be?

00:33:28.230 --> 00:33:29.230
We were watching all along

00:33:29.230 --> 00:33:31.230
And we saw him in here

00:33:31.230 --> 00:33:32.230
Subhanallah

00:33:32.230 --> 00:33:33.230
And where is the man?

00:33:33.230 --> 00:33:34.230
Gone

00:33:34.230 --> 00:33:37.230
So news spread in the morning

00:33:37.230 --> 00:33:38.230
In the morning

00:33:38.230 --> 00:33:39.230
Across Quraysh

00:33:39.230 --> 00:33:41.230
That Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:33:41.230 --> 00:33:42.230
Is gone

00:33:42.230 --> 00:33:43.230
He's gone

00:33:43.230 --> 00:33:44.230
What did they do?

00:33:44.230 --> 00:33:45.230
They became mental

00:33:45.230 --> 00:33:47.230
They became mad

00:33:47.230 --> 00:33:50.230
They started preparing little groups of people

00:33:50.230 --> 00:33:51.230
Go this way, go search that way

00:33:51.230 --> 00:33:52.230
Go search this way

00:33:52.230 --> 00:33:54.230
And they heard Abu Bakr is with him

00:33:54.230 --> 00:33:56.230
They announced in Quraysh

00:33:56.230 --> 00:33:58.230
We will give 100 camels

00:33:58.230 --> 00:34:00.230
To anyone who brings this man back

00:34:00.230 --> 00:34:02.230
Dead or alive

00:34:02.230 --> 00:34:04.230
100 camels

00:34:04.230 --> 00:34:06.230
And the same applies to his companion

00:34:06.230 --> 00:34:08.230
Abu Bakr الصديق رضي الله عنه

00:34:08.230 --> 00:34:09.230
According to some narrations

00:34:09.230 --> 00:34:10.230
The 100 camels

00:34:10.230 --> 00:34:11.230
For either one of them

00:34:11.230 --> 00:34:13.230
And we ask Allah سبحانه وتعالى

00:34:13.230 --> 00:34:14.230
To protect us the way

00:34:14.230 --> 00:34:16.230
He protected Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:34:16.230 --> 00:34:18.230
So Quraysh were very intelligent

00:34:18.230 --> 00:34:21.230
Now a point of importance is

00:34:21.230 --> 00:34:23.230
Abu Bakr الصديق رضي الله عنه

00:34:23.230 --> 00:34:25.230
Had one of his servants

00:34:25.230 --> 00:34:27.230
By the name of Amir ibn Fuhairah

00:34:27.230 --> 00:34:30.230
And this man, he was a shepherd, servant

00:34:30.230 --> 00:34:32.230
And he used to take the sheep to graze

00:34:32.230 --> 00:34:34.230
He was instructed that

00:34:34.230 --> 00:34:38.230
You must graze your sheep near this cave

00:34:38.230 --> 00:34:40.230
And one of the reasons would be

00:34:40.230 --> 00:34:42.230
That you see the footsteps

00:34:42.230 --> 00:34:44.230
Of these men who walked to the cave

00:34:44.230 --> 00:34:46.230
Will be looked at by Quraysh

00:34:46.230 --> 00:34:48.230
Once you have sheep walk all over it

00:34:48.230 --> 00:34:50.230
It becomes very difficult for them to notice

00:34:50.230 --> 00:34:52.230
Look at the planning

00:34:52.230 --> 00:34:55.230
Look at the planning so perfect

00:34:55.230 --> 00:34:56.230
Subhanallah

00:34:56.230 --> 00:34:58.230
From Allah سبحانه وتعالى

00:34:58.230 --> 00:35:00.230
So this Amir ibn Fuhairah

00:35:00.230 --> 00:35:01.230
He took his sheep

00:35:01.230 --> 00:35:03.230
And they walked all over these footsteps

00:35:03.230 --> 00:35:04.230
And so on

00:35:04.230 --> 00:35:06.230
But Quraysh, they were too intelligent

00:35:06.230 --> 00:35:07.230
They had their intelligence

00:35:07.230 --> 00:35:09.230
So they were looking all over

00:35:09.230 --> 00:35:11.230
Until some sort of signs

00:35:11.230 --> 00:35:14.230
Some sort of signs led them to the cave

00:35:14.230 --> 00:35:18.230
And this all was a plan of Allah سبحانه وتعالى

00:35:18.230 --> 00:35:20.230
For Allah سبحانه وتعالى

00:35:20.230 --> 00:35:24.230
To teach us a lesson here today

00:35:24.230 --> 00:35:25.230
That Allah سبحانه وتعالى

00:35:25.230 --> 00:35:27.230
If He protects you

00:35:27.230 --> 00:35:29.230
Wallahi, wallahi

00:35:29.230 --> 00:35:31.230
Nobody can harm you

00:35:31.230 --> 00:35:32.230
Not at all

00:35:32.230 --> 00:35:33.230
And believe me

00:35:33.230 --> 00:35:34.230
People can become blinded

00:35:34.230 --> 00:35:36.230
That you are standing there

00:35:36.230 --> 00:35:38.230
And people can become blinded from your wealth

00:35:38.230 --> 00:35:40.230
That they are trying to steal

00:35:40.230 --> 00:35:42.230
Although it will be glaring them in their faces

00:35:42.230 --> 00:35:43.230
That is if Allah wills

00:35:43.230 --> 00:35:44.230
He has done it

00:35:44.230 --> 00:35:45.230
And He continues doing it

00:35:45.230 --> 00:35:47.230
May Allah protect us

00:35:47.230 --> 00:35:49.230
So Rasulullah صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:35:49.230 --> 00:35:50.230
In the cave

00:35:50.230 --> 00:35:52.230
With Abu Bakr As-Siddiq رضي الله عنه

00:35:52.230 --> 00:35:54.230
The two of them were there

00:35:54.230 --> 00:35:56.230
And Allah سبحانه وتعالى

00:35:56.230 --> 00:35:58.230
Makes mention of what happened

00:35:58.230 --> 00:36:00.230
In that particular cave

00:36:01.230 --> 00:36:04.230
إلا تنصروه

00:36:04.230 --> 00:36:07.230
فقد نصره الله

00:36:07.230 --> 00:36:12.230
إذ أخرجه الذين كفو ثاني اثنين

00:36:12.230 --> 00:36:14.230
إذ هما في الغار

00:36:14.230 --> 00:36:16.230
إذ يقول لصاحبه

00:36:16.230 --> 00:36:21.230
لا تحزن إن الله معنا

00:36:21.230 --> 00:36:26.230
فأنزل الله سكينته عليه

00:36:26.230 --> 00:36:28.230
وأيده بجنود

00:36:29.230 --> 00:36:31.230
الله أكبر

00:36:31.230 --> 00:36:33.230
Allah says if you are not going to assist

00:36:33.230 --> 00:36:35.230
Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:36:35.230 --> 00:36:37.230
Allah has helped him in the past

00:36:37.230 --> 00:36:40.230
When there were two of them in the cave

00:36:40.230 --> 00:36:43.230
And his companion

00:36:43.230 --> 00:36:46.230
Who is Abu Bakr As-Siddiq رضي الله عنه

00:36:46.230 --> 00:36:50.230
Was told do not fear Allah is with us

00:36:50.230 --> 00:36:53.230
Do not fear Allah is with us

00:36:53.230 --> 00:36:55.230
And Allah says we sent to them

00:36:55.230 --> 00:36:58.230
We sent to them armies

00:36:58.230 --> 00:37:00.230
That were not seen

00:37:00.230 --> 00:37:03.230
We sent to them armies that were not seen

00:37:03.230 --> 00:37:04.230
Allah protected them

00:37:04.230 --> 00:37:06.230
Quraish, their members

00:37:06.230 --> 00:37:10.230
Had got right to the mouth of the cave

00:37:10.230 --> 00:37:13.230
They were quite convinced that this is roughly the track

00:37:13.230 --> 00:37:15.230
Where these people are

00:37:15.230 --> 00:37:17.230
Because they looked up and down these roads

00:37:17.230 --> 00:37:19.230
And pathways going to Madinah

00:37:19.230 --> 00:37:20.230
There was no one

00:37:20.230 --> 00:37:21.230
They looked in other directions as well

00:37:21.230 --> 00:37:22.230
No sign

00:37:22.230 --> 00:37:24.230
So this was the only thing

00:37:24.230 --> 00:37:26.230
And Abu Bakr As-Siddiq رضي الله عنه

00:37:26.230 --> 00:37:28.230
Looks at Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:37:28.230 --> 00:37:32.230
He says if these people have to look down

00:37:32.230 --> 00:37:34.230
They will see us

00:37:34.230 --> 00:37:36.230
If these people have to look properly

00:37:36.230 --> 00:37:37.230
They will see us

00:37:37.230 --> 00:37:39.230
And this is when Allah says

00:37:39.230 --> 00:37:41.230
That Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:37:41.230 --> 00:37:42.230
Was instructed to tell him

00:37:42.230 --> 00:37:43.230
لا تحزن

00:37:43.230 --> 00:37:44.230
Don't be sad

00:37:44.230 --> 00:37:45.230
إِنَّ اللَّهَ مَعَنَ

00:37:45.230 --> 00:37:46.230
Allah is with us

00:37:46.230 --> 00:37:47.230
So the verse says

00:37:47.230 --> 00:37:50.230
فَأَنزَلَ اللَّهُ سَكِينَتَهُ عَلَيْهُ

00:37:50.230 --> 00:37:52.230
Allah then sent down the tranquility

00:37:52.230 --> 00:37:54.230
And the peace upon him

00:37:54.230 --> 00:37:55.230
Upon not only his messenger

00:37:55.230 --> 00:37:56.230
Who was already that

00:37:56.230 --> 00:37:59.230
But even Abu Bakr As-Siddiq رضي الله عنه

00:37:59.230 --> 00:38:02.230
Who was calm and relaxed

00:38:02.230 --> 00:38:05.230
Now there is mention made

00:38:05.230 --> 00:38:10.230
Of a spider and a dove

00:38:10.230 --> 00:38:13.230
There is mention made in the books of history

00:38:13.230 --> 00:38:15.230
Not in the books of hadith

00:38:15.230 --> 00:38:17.230
I hope you can see the difference between the two

00:38:17.230 --> 00:38:20.230
The books of history make mention of a spider

00:38:20.230 --> 00:38:23.230
That spun its web in a way

00:38:23.230 --> 00:38:24.230
That the people of Quraysh

00:38:24.230 --> 00:38:26.230
It is said they asked a question

00:38:26.230 --> 00:38:28.230
How can they be in here

00:38:28.230 --> 00:38:30.230
If there is a spider web

00:38:30.230 --> 00:38:33.230
Because a spider web wouldn't be here already

00:38:33.230 --> 00:38:35.230
It would have needed some time

00:38:35.230 --> 00:38:36.230
So it shows

00:38:36.230 --> 00:38:38.230
You know when you walk into your home

00:38:38.230 --> 00:38:39.230
And there's all webs

00:38:39.230 --> 00:38:41.230
It means there's been no one there for a while

00:38:41.230 --> 00:38:43.230
And the same applies to a nest

00:38:43.230 --> 00:38:45.230
Of a little pigeon or dove

00:38:45.230 --> 00:38:47.230
But for your information

00:38:47.230 --> 00:38:49.230
As for the pigeon or dove

00:38:49.230 --> 00:38:51.230
Even the books of history make mention

00:38:51.230 --> 00:38:53.230
That the narration is not authentic

00:38:53.230 --> 00:38:57.230
And as for the spinning of the web

00:38:57.230 --> 00:38:59.230
It is made mention in the books of Seerah

00:38:59.230 --> 00:39:01.230
But not in the books of hadith

00:39:01.230 --> 00:39:03.230
And the Muhaddithin still say

00:39:03.230 --> 00:39:04.230
That it is highly debatable

00:39:04.230 --> 00:39:06.230
Although some of the scholars say

00:39:06.230 --> 00:39:08.230
No, it is authentic for me and you

00:39:08.230 --> 00:39:10.230
Alhamdulillah we surrender and we say

00:39:10.230 --> 00:39:13.230
Allah protected them with armies

00:39:13.230 --> 00:39:16.230
And Allah's armies include the birds

00:39:16.230 --> 00:39:19.230
And the spiders and the angels

00:39:19.230 --> 00:39:21.230
And anyone else whom Allah wants

00:39:21.230 --> 00:39:23.230
What happened is they were protected

00:39:23.230 --> 00:39:24.230
Subhanallah

00:39:24.230 --> 00:39:26.230
So Alhamdulillah the Quraysh

00:39:26.230 --> 00:39:28.230
Then looked this way that way and turned around

00:39:28.230 --> 00:39:30.230
When they turned around and went away

00:39:30.230 --> 00:39:32.230
And after some time on the third day

00:39:32.230 --> 00:39:33.230
What happened

00:39:33.230 --> 00:39:35.230
This man comes with the two camels

00:39:35.230 --> 00:39:38.230
By the third day the hunt had been already

00:39:38.230 --> 00:39:40.230
You know calmed down

00:39:40.230 --> 00:39:42.230
And all the hype of it was all gone

00:39:42.230 --> 00:39:44.230
And now this man

00:39:45.230 --> 00:39:49.230
He comes with the two camels

00:39:49.230 --> 00:39:51.230
And he is ready to pick up Rasulullah

00:39:51.230 --> 00:39:52.230
Sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:39:52.230 --> 00:39:55.230
In the meantime for the amount of days

00:39:55.230 --> 00:39:57.230
What was happening is the son

00:39:57.230 --> 00:39:59.230
Of Abu Bakr as-Siddiq radiallahu anhu

00:39:59.230 --> 00:40:00.230
Who was a young boy

00:40:00.230 --> 00:40:02.230
Abdullah ibn Abi Bakr

00:40:02.230 --> 00:40:04.230
He was tasked with something by his father

00:40:04.230 --> 00:40:06.230
His father told him as he was leaving

00:40:06.230 --> 00:40:07.230
Listen my son

00:40:07.230 --> 00:40:09.230
During the daytime you must walk around by Quraysh

00:40:09.230 --> 00:40:11.230
See what they're saying about us

00:40:11.230 --> 00:40:12.230
And what's happening

00:40:12.230 --> 00:40:14.230
Bring us some news in the night

00:40:14.230 --> 00:40:16.230
And this young boy used to actually do that

00:40:16.230 --> 00:40:19.230
So this was just to find out what was happening

00:40:19.230 --> 00:40:21.230
And to know that these people heading

00:40:21.230 --> 00:40:23.230
In the wrong direction and in that direction

00:40:23.230 --> 00:40:24.230
And this and that and so on

00:40:24.230 --> 00:40:26.230
So then they had given up at a certain point

00:40:26.230 --> 00:40:28.230
And then as we mentioned

00:40:28.230 --> 00:40:30.230
The daughter of Abu Bakr as-Siddiq radiallahu anhu

00:40:30.230 --> 00:40:33.230
Came to help Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:40:33.230 --> 00:40:35.230
And his father with some food

00:40:35.230 --> 00:40:36.230
And this had happened

00:40:36.230 --> 00:40:38.230
She used to come quietly walking out

00:40:38.230 --> 00:40:40.230
And then she would go and deliver the food

00:40:40.230 --> 00:40:41.230
Come back and so on

00:40:41.230 --> 00:40:43.230
And this was the group of people

00:40:43.230 --> 00:40:45.230
Mainly made up of the family

00:40:45.230 --> 00:40:48.230
Of Abu Bakr as-Siddiq radiallahu anhu

00:40:48.230 --> 00:40:51.230
When the day the prophet sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:40:51.230 --> 00:40:53.230
Told him in his home that

00:40:53.230 --> 00:40:55.230
I have been permitted to leave

00:40:55.230 --> 00:40:56.230
The first thing he said

00:40:56.230 --> 00:40:58.230
As-Suhbatu ya Rasoolallah

00:40:58.230 --> 00:41:00.230
Can I be your companion or messenger

00:41:00.230 --> 00:41:01.230
Sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:41:01.230 --> 00:41:02.230
He said yes indeed

00:41:02.230 --> 00:41:04.230
And this is when he became the companion

00:41:04.230 --> 00:41:06.230
Of Rasoolallah sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:41:06.230 --> 00:41:09.230
And we believe not only the companion

00:41:09.230 --> 00:41:10.230
In his life

00:41:10.230 --> 00:41:11.230
But even in the death

00:41:11.230 --> 00:41:14.230
He is buried right next to Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:41:14.230 --> 00:41:16.230
Abu Bakr as-Siddiq radiallahu anhu

00:41:16.230 --> 00:41:18.230
The best of those who tread this earth

00:41:18.230 --> 00:41:21.230
After the prophets of Allah sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:41:21.230 --> 00:41:24.230
So thereafter they started their journey

00:41:24.230 --> 00:41:25.230
And alhamdulillah

00:41:25.230 --> 00:41:27.230
The journey was a beautiful journey

00:41:27.230 --> 00:41:31.230
Which the guide intelligently took them

00:41:31.230 --> 00:41:33.230
On a different route altogether

00:41:33.230 --> 00:41:34.230
Not on the normal route

00:41:34.230 --> 00:41:37.230
Because he realized these people are going to Medina

00:41:37.230 --> 00:41:40.230
Then let me take them on a longer route

00:41:40.230 --> 00:41:43.230
On the coast, the coastal road

00:41:43.230 --> 00:41:45.230
And this is why today

00:41:45.230 --> 00:41:48.230
People can actually choose to use the old road

00:41:48.230 --> 00:41:50.230
Which goes via Badr and so on

00:41:50.230 --> 00:41:54.230
To go back into Makkah al-Mukarrama from Medina or vice versa

00:41:54.230 --> 00:41:58.230
Although the highway is built more or less straight

00:41:58.230 --> 00:42:00.230
But when it comes to the old road

00:42:00.230 --> 00:42:04.230
It's not even the road which was taken by Rasoolallah sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:42:04.230 --> 00:42:07.230
Because that one was never developed as such later on

00:42:07.230 --> 00:42:11.230
It is further in and it follows the coast

00:42:11.230 --> 00:42:14.230
So as they were traveling

00:42:14.230 --> 00:42:17.230
Some miracles happened which we must make mention

00:42:17.230 --> 00:42:19.230
One of the first miracles that had happened

00:42:19.230 --> 00:42:21.230
Subhanallah

00:42:21.230 --> 00:42:23.230
News had got around everywhere

00:42:23.230 --> 00:42:25.230
Quraish had sent their horsemen here and there

00:42:25.230 --> 00:42:27.230
Telling everyone 100 camels

00:42:27.230 --> 00:42:29.230
100 camels is a big deal

00:42:29.230 --> 00:42:32.230
It's like me telling you 100 million dollars

00:42:32.230 --> 00:42:33.230
Basically

00:42:33.230 --> 00:42:35.230
A large amount of money

00:42:35.230 --> 00:42:37.230
And everyone, subhanallah

00:42:37.230 --> 00:42:39.230
Was looking out for these people

00:42:39.230 --> 00:42:41.230
Because we are going to get 100 camels

00:42:41.230 --> 00:42:43.230
100 camels we are going to get

00:42:43.230 --> 00:42:46.230
And there was a certain place

00:42:46.230 --> 00:42:48.230
Where a man who was a bounty hunter

00:42:48.230 --> 00:42:49.230
You know what's a bounty hunter

00:42:49.230 --> 00:42:51.230
A person who looks for this type of thing

00:42:51.230 --> 00:42:52.230
And then he goes and hunts for those people

00:42:52.230 --> 00:42:54.230
And brings them dead or alive

00:42:54.230 --> 00:42:56.230
To make the money out of it

00:42:56.230 --> 00:42:59.230
His name was Suraka ibn Malik

00:42:59.230 --> 00:43:01.230
This Suraka ibn Malik was sitting

00:43:01.230 --> 00:43:02.230
Amongst his friends

00:43:02.230 --> 00:43:03.230
One comes up and says

00:43:03.230 --> 00:43:04.230
You know what

00:43:04.230 --> 00:43:05.230
On that particular road on the coast

00:43:05.230 --> 00:43:07.230
I'm sure I saw some people

00:43:07.230 --> 00:43:09.230
And that must be Muhammad and his companions

00:43:09.230 --> 00:43:10.230
And you know

00:43:10.230 --> 00:43:12.230
So Suraka heard it

00:43:12.230 --> 00:43:14.230
Very sharp, intelligent man

00:43:14.230 --> 00:43:15.230
He immediately said

00:43:15.230 --> 00:43:16.230
No, no, that's somebody else

00:43:16.230 --> 00:43:17.230
I know those people

00:43:17.230 --> 00:43:18.230
It's somebody else

00:43:18.230 --> 00:43:19.230
It's not them and so on

00:43:19.230 --> 00:43:20.230
And the topic died

00:43:20.230 --> 00:43:21.230
Soon as that happened

00:43:21.230 --> 00:43:24.230
He got up, got his horse and he ran

00:43:24.230 --> 00:43:25.230
So he was cheating

00:43:25.230 --> 00:43:27.230
He actually knew that yes it might be

00:43:27.230 --> 00:43:30.230
But to divert the man who brought the news

00:43:30.230 --> 00:43:31.230
And to get the money for himself

00:43:31.230 --> 00:43:33.230
And the camels for himself

00:43:33.230 --> 00:43:34.230
What did he say?

00:43:34.230 --> 00:43:35.230
He said no, no

00:43:35.230 --> 00:43:36.230
It's not them

00:43:36.230 --> 00:43:37.230
I know it's not them

00:43:37.230 --> 00:43:39.230
And then as soon as that man turned around

00:43:39.230 --> 00:43:40.230
And everything died down a little bit

00:43:40.230 --> 00:43:42.230
This man goes and he

00:43:42.230 --> 00:43:46.230
As he is racing with his horse

00:43:46.230 --> 00:43:47.230
He's racing with his horse

00:43:47.230 --> 00:43:48.230
And he sees them

00:43:48.230 --> 00:43:49.230
And he notices

00:43:49.230 --> 00:43:51.230
And he notices from amongst them

00:43:51.230 --> 00:43:52.230
The Prophet sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:43:52.230 --> 00:43:53.230
Is not looking back

00:43:53.230 --> 00:43:55.230
And Abu Bakr as-Siddiq radiallahu anhu

00:43:55.230 --> 00:43:57.230
Looks back now and again

00:43:57.230 --> 00:43:59.230
And as he sees them

00:43:59.230 --> 00:44:03.230
Then his horse trips and drops

00:44:03.230 --> 00:44:04.230
And then he gets it up

00:44:04.230 --> 00:44:05.230
He gets back up on it

00:44:05.230 --> 00:44:06.230
And he starts going again

00:44:06.230 --> 00:44:08.230
And the horse has slowed down

00:44:08.230 --> 00:44:09.230
And it's like he doesn't want to move

00:44:09.230 --> 00:44:11.230
And this is an authentic narration

00:44:11.230 --> 00:44:12.230
Subhanallah

00:44:12.230 --> 00:44:13.230
Suraqa bin Malik

00:44:13.230 --> 00:44:15.230
He makes mention of it later on as well

00:44:15.230 --> 00:44:16.230
And what happened is

00:44:16.230 --> 00:44:18.230
This man says after some time

00:44:18.230 --> 00:44:20.230
When I was about to get to them

00:44:20.230 --> 00:44:22.230
I got through some quick sand

00:44:22.230 --> 00:44:25.230
And my horse started sinking in the sand

00:44:25.230 --> 00:44:26.230
And so I got off the horse

00:44:26.230 --> 00:44:28.230
And I managed to take this horse out

00:44:28.230 --> 00:44:29.230
With great difficulty

00:44:29.230 --> 00:44:30.230
By that time these people

00:44:30.230 --> 00:44:31.230
Had gone even further

00:44:31.230 --> 00:44:32.230
And I got onto it

00:44:32.230 --> 00:44:33.230
And I started going again

00:44:33.230 --> 00:44:34.230
And as I'm going

00:44:34.230 --> 00:44:37.230
A huge cloud of dust comes up

00:44:37.230 --> 00:44:39.230
And some smoke as I couldn't even see

00:44:39.230 --> 00:44:41.230
What was happening from the skies

00:44:41.230 --> 00:44:42.230
And I told myself

00:44:42.230 --> 00:44:43.230
No, these people

00:44:43.230 --> 00:44:45.230
I'm never going to reach them

00:44:45.230 --> 00:44:46.230
This man is protected

00:44:46.230 --> 00:44:48.230
This man is protected

00:44:48.230 --> 00:44:49.230
Subhanallah

00:44:49.230 --> 00:44:51.230
This is America

00:44:51.230 --> 00:44:53.230
And what had happened is

00:44:53.230 --> 00:44:55.230
Suraqa bin Malik then yells

00:44:55.230 --> 00:44:57.230
He screams in a way that they can hear

00:44:57.230 --> 00:44:59.230
He says look I promised not to harm you

00:44:59.230 --> 00:45:00.230
And at the same time

00:45:00.230 --> 00:45:01.230
I would not like harm from you

00:45:01.230 --> 00:45:03.230
I want a guarantee

00:45:03.230 --> 00:45:04.230
And you are guaranteed

00:45:04.230 --> 00:45:06.230
So they slowed down

00:45:06.230 --> 00:45:07.230
They managed to get hold of him

00:45:07.230 --> 00:45:08.230
And he came

00:45:08.230 --> 00:45:09.230
And they spoke to each other

00:45:09.230 --> 00:45:10.230
And he gave them the news

00:45:10.230 --> 00:45:11.230
What was the news?

00:45:11.230 --> 00:45:13.230
You people are being sought after

00:45:13.230 --> 00:45:15.230
There is a hundred camels behind you

00:45:15.230 --> 00:45:17.230
I obviously there was now a guarantee

00:45:17.230 --> 00:45:18.230
I'm not going to touch you

00:45:18.230 --> 00:45:20.230
But what's going to happen?

00:45:20.230 --> 00:45:22.230
I'm going to go back

00:45:22.230 --> 00:45:23.230
Can you give me a note

00:45:23.230 --> 00:45:25.230
To guarantee me and my safety

00:45:25.230 --> 00:45:27.230
Because now that I've met you

00:45:27.230 --> 00:45:28.230
What if some of your people see me

00:45:28.230 --> 00:45:29.230
Whatever it was

00:45:29.230 --> 00:45:31.230
Abu Bakr as-Siddiq radiAllahu anhu

00:45:31.230 --> 00:45:32.230
Was instructed by the messenger

00:45:32.230 --> 00:45:34.230
To write a little note of guarantee

00:45:34.230 --> 00:45:35.230
For this particular man

00:45:35.230 --> 00:45:37.230
And Suraqa bin Malik

00:45:37.230 --> 00:45:38.230
It's reported that thereafter

00:45:38.230 --> 00:45:40.230
He went away

00:45:40.230 --> 00:45:42.230
This man did not become a Muslim

00:45:42.230 --> 00:45:43.230
He saw the miracles

00:45:43.230 --> 00:45:45.230
But the day when the Muslims

00:45:45.230 --> 00:45:48.230
Returned to Mecca victorious

00:45:48.230 --> 00:45:49.230
That's the day he accepted Islam

00:45:49.230 --> 00:45:51.230
This Suraqa bin Malik

00:45:51.230 --> 00:45:52.230
And then we found out

00:45:52.230 --> 00:45:53.230
What happened in his life

00:45:53.230 --> 00:45:54.230
And the whole story

00:45:54.230 --> 00:45:55.230
He says it himself

00:45:55.230 --> 00:45:57.230
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:45:57.230 --> 00:45:58.230
Grant us protection

00:45:58.230 --> 00:46:00.230
So Allah protected Muhammad

00:46:00.230 --> 00:46:01.230
SallAllahu alayhi wa sallam

00:46:01.230 --> 00:46:02.230
In that way

00:46:02.230 --> 00:46:04.230
The next miracle that had happened

00:46:04.230 --> 00:46:06.230
There was a lady in a place

00:46:06.230 --> 00:46:07.230
Known as Qudeid

00:46:07.230 --> 00:46:10.230
And her name was Atika bint Khalaf

00:46:10.230 --> 00:46:12.230
Also known as Ummu Ma'bad

00:46:12.230 --> 00:46:15.230
And there are two narrations

00:46:15.230 --> 00:46:16.230
One of them says that

00:46:16.230 --> 00:46:18.230
Abu Ma'bad who is the man

00:46:18.230 --> 00:46:19.230
The husband was not at home

00:46:19.230 --> 00:46:20.230
And the other one says

00:46:20.230 --> 00:46:21.230
No he was at home

00:46:21.230 --> 00:46:23.230
And the more correct narration

00:46:23.230 --> 00:46:24.230
Says he was at home

00:46:24.230 --> 00:46:25.230
So what happened is

00:46:25.230 --> 00:46:27.230
The Prophet SallAllahu alayhi wa sallam

00:46:27.230 --> 00:46:28.230
They stopped at a specific place

00:46:28.230 --> 00:46:29.230
Here in Qudeid

00:46:29.230 --> 00:46:31.230
And they asked for some food

00:46:31.230 --> 00:46:33.230
And some drink and so on

00:46:33.230 --> 00:46:34.230
And they were told

00:46:34.230 --> 00:46:35.230
Look you know what

00:46:35.230 --> 00:46:36.230
We don't have any here

00:46:36.230 --> 00:46:38.230
We've only got these sheep

00:46:38.230 --> 00:46:39.230
That are here

00:46:39.230 --> 00:46:40.230
That do not have much

00:46:40.230 --> 00:46:41.230
They don't have any milk

00:46:41.230 --> 00:46:43.230
And some of them are pregnant

00:46:43.230 --> 00:46:44.230
And so on

00:46:44.230 --> 00:46:45.230
They don't have milk

00:46:45.230 --> 00:46:47.230
Now up to that point

00:46:47.230 --> 00:46:49.230
Rasulullah SallAllahu alayhi wa sallam's

00:46:49.230 --> 00:46:50.230
Group

00:46:50.230 --> 00:46:51.230
Meaning the group of people

00:46:51.230 --> 00:46:52.230
Who were with

00:46:52.230 --> 00:46:53.230
The guide

00:46:53.230 --> 00:46:55.230
Abu Bakr as-Siddiq radiAllahu anhu

00:46:55.230 --> 00:46:56.230
And the Prophet SallAllahu alayhi wa sallam

00:46:56.230 --> 00:46:58.230
They were very very careful

00:46:58.230 --> 00:47:00.230
Answering questions

00:47:00.230 --> 00:47:01.230
When someone asks

00:47:01.230 --> 00:47:03.230
Abu Bakr as-Siddiq radiAllahu anhu

00:47:03.230 --> 00:47:04.230
Who is the man with you

00:47:04.230 --> 00:47:05.230
He would say

00:47:05.230 --> 00:47:06.230
He is my guide

00:47:06.230 --> 00:47:08.230
My guide meaning spiritual guide

00:47:08.230 --> 00:47:09.230
But they would think

00:47:09.230 --> 00:47:10.230
The guide of the road

00:47:10.230 --> 00:47:13.230
Yet he was Muhammad SallAllahu alayhi wa sallam

00:47:13.230 --> 00:47:14.230
Because they wanted to know

00:47:14.230 --> 00:47:15.230
Who is this man

00:47:15.230 --> 00:47:17.230
And he was obviously

00:47:17.230 --> 00:47:18.230
In such a way that

00:47:18.230 --> 00:47:19.230
People would not see him

00:47:19.230 --> 00:47:21.230
If they did not trust someone

00:47:21.230 --> 00:47:23.230
Then they wouldn't unnecessarily

00:47:23.230 --> 00:47:24.230
Turn around and so on

00:47:24.230 --> 00:47:25.230
Like we heard

00:47:25.230 --> 00:47:26.230
What Surah bin Malik says

00:47:26.230 --> 00:47:28.230
That this man did not turn

00:47:28.230 --> 00:47:29.230
But Abu Bakr radiAllahu anhu

00:47:29.230 --> 00:47:32.230
Kept turning every now and again

00:47:32.230 --> 00:47:33.230
So at this point

00:47:33.230 --> 00:47:34.230
When they stopped for

00:47:34.230 --> 00:47:36.230
A little bit of food and drink

00:47:36.230 --> 00:47:38.230
Then the Prophet SallAllahu alayhi wa sallam

00:47:38.230 --> 00:47:39.230
Spoke

00:47:39.230 --> 00:47:40.230
And he says

00:47:40.230 --> 00:47:41.230
To Abu Ma'bad

00:47:41.230 --> 00:47:42.230
One narration says

00:47:42.230 --> 00:47:43.230
Abu Ma'bad was not there

00:47:43.230 --> 00:47:44.230
So he spoke to Umm Ma'bad

00:47:44.230 --> 00:47:45.230
But we will go with

00:47:45.230 --> 00:47:47.230
The more authentic narration

00:47:47.230 --> 00:47:48.230
He spoke to Abu Ma'bad

00:47:48.230 --> 00:47:49.230
And he says

00:47:49.230 --> 00:47:50.230
What about this

00:47:50.230 --> 00:47:51.230
Sheet that's there

00:47:51.230 --> 00:47:52.230
He says

00:47:52.230 --> 00:47:53.230
Look it's dry

00:47:53.230 --> 00:47:54.230
There's no milk at all

00:47:54.230 --> 00:47:56.230
So Muhammad SallAllahu alayhi wa sallam says

00:47:56.230 --> 00:47:57.230
Would you mind

00:47:57.230 --> 00:47:59.230
If I try to milk it

00:47:59.230 --> 00:48:01.230
So the Rasulullah SallAllahu alayhi wa sallam

00:48:01.230 --> 00:48:02.230
Was told

00:48:02.230 --> 00:48:03.230
No problem

00:48:03.230 --> 00:48:04.230
You can milk it

00:48:04.230 --> 00:48:05.230
When it came

00:48:05.230 --> 00:48:07.230
He put his hand on the others

00:48:07.230 --> 00:48:08.230
He made a dua

00:48:08.230 --> 00:48:10.230
For baraka and goodness

00:48:10.230 --> 00:48:12.230
And suddenly the others became full

00:48:12.230 --> 00:48:13.230
He milked it

00:48:13.230 --> 00:48:14.230
So much milk came out

00:48:14.230 --> 00:48:16.230
They all drank

00:48:16.230 --> 00:48:17.230
The family drank

00:48:17.230 --> 00:48:18.230
The people drank

00:48:18.230 --> 00:48:19.230
They all drank

00:48:19.230 --> 00:48:20.230
They were okay

00:48:20.230 --> 00:48:22.230
And when they were finished drinking

00:48:22.230 --> 00:48:23.230
He milked it

00:48:23.230 --> 00:48:24.230
According to the narration

00:48:24.230 --> 00:48:26.230
Once again for a surplus of milk

00:48:26.230 --> 00:48:27.230
Subhanallah

00:48:27.230 --> 00:48:30.230
And this Abu Ma'bad looks and says

00:48:30.230 --> 00:48:32.230
Are you not the man

00:48:32.230 --> 00:48:34.230
That Quraish is looking for

00:48:34.230 --> 00:48:35.230
You are not the man

00:48:35.230 --> 00:48:37.230
Who has reneged from the religion

00:48:37.230 --> 00:48:38.230
Of the forefathers

00:48:38.230 --> 00:48:40.230
And Rasulullah SallAllahu alayhi wa sallam

00:48:40.230 --> 00:48:41.230
Within his heart

00:48:41.230 --> 00:48:42.230
He knew

00:48:42.230 --> 00:48:44.230
That this person here

00:48:44.230 --> 00:48:45.230
Is about to enter

00:48:45.230 --> 00:48:46.230
The fold of Islam

00:48:46.230 --> 00:48:47.230
So he said

00:48:47.230 --> 00:48:48.230
Well, so they say

00:48:48.230 --> 00:48:50.230
That I was a renegade

00:48:50.230 --> 00:48:51.230
And I did this and that

00:48:51.230 --> 00:48:52.230
And I am the man

00:48:52.230 --> 00:48:53.230
They are looking for

00:48:53.230 --> 00:48:54.230
He says

00:48:54.230 --> 00:48:55.230
I bear witness

00:48:55.230 --> 00:48:56.230
That you are a prophet

00:48:56.230 --> 00:48:57.230
You are the messenger

00:48:57.230 --> 00:48:58.230
I have seen

00:48:58.230 --> 00:48:59.230
That's it

00:48:59.230 --> 00:49:00.230
Subhanallah

00:49:00.230 --> 00:49:01.230
Amazing

00:49:01.230 --> 00:49:02.230
The other narration says

00:49:02.230 --> 00:49:03.230
That he was away

00:49:03.230 --> 00:49:05.230
But this happened to his wife

00:49:05.230 --> 00:49:07.230
And when his wife told him

00:49:07.230 --> 00:49:08.230
What happened

00:49:08.230 --> 00:49:09.230
He said

00:49:09.230 --> 00:49:10.230
That was the man

00:49:10.230 --> 00:49:11.230
And I will follow him

00:49:11.230 --> 00:49:13.230
If I can inshallah

00:49:13.230 --> 00:49:15.230
But the more correct narration

00:49:15.230 --> 00:49:16.230
Says

00:49:16.230 --> 00:49:17.230
He immediately said

00:49:17.230 --> 00:49:18.230
Can I not join you people

00:49:18.230 --> 00:49:19.230
You are going to Madinah

00:49:19.230 --> 00:49:20.230
Come, I am coming

00:49:20.230 --> 00:49:21.230
I will pack up my things

00:49:21.230 --> 00:49:22.230
And myself and wife

00:49:22.230 --> 00:49:23.230
Will come with you

00:49:23.230 --> 00:49:24.230
And Rasulullah SallAllahu alayhi wa sallam

00:49:24.230 --> 00:49:25.230
Told him

00:49:25.230 --> 00:49:26.230
No

00:49:26.230 --> 00:49:27.230
Wait until the day

00:49:27.230 --> 00:49:28.230
You hear about us

00:49:28.230 --> 00:49:29.230
When you hear

00:49:29.230 --> 00:49:30.230
That we have now come up

00:49:30.230 --> 00:49:31.230
Then you can come to

00:49:31.230 --> 00:49:32.230
Al-Madinah Al-Munawwara

00:49:32.230 --> 00:49:33.230
And true to his word

00:49:33.230 --> 00:49:34.230
He did make it there

00:49:34.230 --> 00:49:35.230
After some time

00:49:35.230 --> 00:49:37.230
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:49:37.230 --> 00:49:38.230
Grant us all goodness

00:49:38.230 --> 00:49:40.230
This was another miracle

00:49:40.230 --> 00:49:42.230
That Rasulullah SallAllahu alayhi wa sallam

00:49:42.230 --> 00:49:43.230
Was granted

00:49:43.230 --> 00:49:44.230
Also it is reported

00:49:44.230 --> 00:49:45.230
In some correct narrations

00:49:45.230 --> 00:49:47.230
That Az-Zubayr ibn al-Awwam

00:49:47.230 --> 00:49:48.230
As he was coming back

00:49:48.230 --> 00:49:49.230
From his journey

00:49:49.230 --> 00:49:50.230
And his travel

00:49:50.230 --> 00:49:51.230
Had met this caravan

00:49:51.230 --> 00:49:54.230
Of Rasulullah SallAllahu alayhi wa sallam

00:49:54.230 --> 00:49:55.230
We say caravan

00:49:55.230 --> 00:49:56.230
We speaking of two camels

00:49:56.230 --> 00:49:58.230
Perhaps a third one

00:49:58.230 --> 00:49:59.230
And he met them

00:49:59.230 --> 00:50:00.230
And he gave them

00:50:00.230 --> 00:50:01.230
Some clothing and so on

00:50:01.230 --> 00:50:03.230
This was Az-Zubayr ibn al-Awwam

00:50:03.230 --> 00:50:04.230
Who was a Sahabi

00:50:04.230 --> 00:50:06.230
RadhiAllahu anhu

00:50:06.230 --> 00:50:09.230
Returning from one of his journeys

00:50:09.230 --> 00:50:12.230
Then comes the historic occasion

00:50:12.230 --> 00:50:14.230
When the Prophet SallAllahu alayhi wa sallam

00:50:14.230 --> 00:50:16.230
On a Monday

00:50:16.230 --> 00:50:18.230
Arrived in Quba

00:50:18.230 --> 00:50:20.230
The outskirts of Madinah Munawwara

00:50:20.230 --> 00:50:23.230
From a distance

00:50:23.230 --> 00:50:24.230
Every day the people

00:50:24.230 --> 00:50:26.230
Used to come out and look

00:50:26.230 --> 00:50:27.230
Where are these people?

00:50:27.230 --> 00:50:28.230
Perhaps we'll see them

00:50:28.230 --> 00:50:29.230
Perhaps we'll see them

00:50:29.230 --> 00:50:31.230
On that day

00:50:31.230 --> 00:50:32.230
They had waited

00:50:32.230 --> 00:50:33.230
It was quite a hot day

00:50:33.230 --> 00:50:35.230
And they were all gone back

00:50:35.230 --> 00:50:36.230
And as the heat

00:50:36.230 --> 00:50:38.230
Became very intense

00:50:38.230 --> 00:50:39.230
Subhanallah

00:50:39.230 --> 00:50:40.230
A Jewish man

00:50:40.230 --> 00:50:42.230
Who had climbed up saw

00:50:42.230 --> 00:50:43.230
And he says

00:50:43.230 --> 00:50:44.230
You know what

00:50:44.230 --> 00:50:45.230
There is your man

00:50:45.230 --> 00:50:46.230
Your man

00:50:46.230 --> 00:50:47.230
You know this

00:50:47.230 --> 00:50:48.230
The term used is like

00:50:48.230 --> 00:50:49.230
Grandfather has arrived

00:50:49.230 --> 00:50:50.230
You know

00:50:50.230 --> 00:50:52.230
Your man has arrived here

00:50:52.230 --> 00:50:54.230
And so they all got excited

00:50:54.230 --> 00:50:55.230
This was Quba

00:50:55.230 --> 00:50:58.230
Quba the outskirts of Madinah Munawwara

00:50:58.230 --> 00:50:59.230
And mashallah

00:50:59.230 --> 00:51:00.230
Tabarakallah

00:51:00.230 --> 00:51:01.230
They all came up

00:51:01.230 --> 00:51:02.230
And they

00:51:02.230 --> 00:51:04.230
Some of them had got their swords

00:51:04.230 --> 00:51:06.230
In order to protect

00:51:06.230 --> 00:51:08.230
Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:51:08.230 --> 00:51:09.230
Just in case

00:51:09.230 --> 00:51:10.230
Something went wrong

00:51:10.230 --> 00:51:11.230
And they went up

00:51:11.230 --> 00:51:12.230
And they were so happy

00:51:12.230 --> 00:51:14.230
They got to Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:51:14.230 --> 00:51:16.230
They got to Abu Bakr as-Siddiq

00:51:16.230 --> 00:51:18.230
Radhiallahu anhu

00:51:18.230 --> 00:51:19.230
And being so excited

00:51:19.230 --> 00:51:20.230
Welcoming them

00:51:20.230 --> 00:51:22.230
Declaring their shahadah

00:51:22.230 --> 00:51:23.230
Declaring the words of

00:51:23.230 --> 00:51:24.230
You know

00:51:24.230 --> 00:51:26.230
Ya Muhammad ya Rasulallah

00:51:26.230 --> 00:51:27.230
And so on

00:51:27.230 --> 00:51:28.230
These were the people of Quba

00:51:28.230 --> 00:51:29.230
Having come out

00:51:29.230 --> 00:51:30.230
The muhajireen from amongst them

00:51:30.230 --> 00:51:32.230
The ansar from amongst them

00:51:32.230 --> 00:51:33.230
Those who were helpers

00:51:33.230 --> 00:51:35.230
From Madinah Munawwara

00:51:35.230 --> 00:51:36.230
And they had come out

00:51:36.230 --> 00:51:37.230
It is reported

00:51:37.230 --> 00:51:38.230
This

00:51:38.230 --> 00:51:39.230
The arrival

00:51:39.230 --> 00:51:40.230
There are many

00:51:40.230 --> 00:51:41.230
Conflicting narrations

00:51:41.230 --> 00:51:42.230
As per the date

00:51:42.230 --> 00:51:43.230
Of arrival

00:51:43.230 --> 00:51:44.230
But one of the most

00:51:44.230 --> 00:51:45.230
Authentic narration states

00:51:45.230 --> 00:51:46.230
That it was a Monday

00:51:46.230 --> 00:51:47.230
The 12th of

00:51:47.230 --> 00:51:49.230
Rabi' al-awwal

00:51:49.230 --> 00:51:50.230
Have you heard that date

00:51:50.230 --> 00:51:51.230
Before somewhere

00:51:51.230 --> 00:51:52.230
Subhanallah

00:51:52.230 --> 00:51:53.230
Coinciding similarly

00:51:53.230 --> 00:51:54.230
To similar date

00:51:54.230 --> 00:51:55.230
As the birth of

00:51:55.230 --> 00:51:57.230
Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:51:57.230 --> 00:51:59.230
So he arrived in Quba

00:51:59.230 --> 00:52:00.230
May Allah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:52:00.230 --> 00:52:01.230
Bless us all

00:52:01.230 --> 00:52:02.230
May Allah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:52:02.230 --> 00:52:04.230
Grant us goodness

00:52:04.230 --> 00:52:05.230
Just to make quick mention

00:52:05.230 --> 00:52:06.230
Of where

00:52:06.230 --> 00:52:07.230
He spent his time

00:52:07.230 --> 00:52:09.230
Whilst he was in Quba

00:52:09.230 --> 00:52:10.230
In Quba

00:52:10.230 --> 00:52:11.230
He stayed between

00:52:11.230 --> 00:52:13.230
14 and 19 days

00:52:13.230 --> 00:52:14.230
And he stayed

00:52:14.230 --> 00:52:15.230
At the house

00:52:15.230 --> 00:52:16.230
Of one of the leaders

00:52:16.230 --> 00:52:17.230
Of Banu Amr

00:52:17.230 --> 00:52:18.230
Whose name was

00:52:18.230 --> 00:52:19.230
Kulthum ibn al-Hidin

00:52:19.230 --> 00:52:20.230
And this man

00:52:20.230 --> 00:52:21.230
Was one of the leaders

00:52:21.230 --> 00:52:23.230
Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:52:23.230 --> 00:52:24.230
Stayed in his home

00:52:24.230 --> 00:52:25.230
And the prophet

00:52:25.230 --> 00:52:26.230
Sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:52:26.230 --> 00:52:28.230
Met with his people

00:52:28.230 --> 00:52:30.230
And lots of goodness

00:52:30.230 --> 00:52:31.230
Was spoken

00:52:31.230 --> 00:52:32.230
Now he was already

00:52:32.230 --> 00:52:34.230
Protected by the people

00:52:34.230 --> 00:52:35.230
Of Madinah Munawwara

00:52:35.230 --> 00:52:37.230
Obviously

00:52:37.230 --> 00:52:38.230
Over and above that

00:52:38.230 --> 00:52:39.230
Was the protection

00:52:39.230 --> 00:52:40.230
Of Allah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:52:40.230 --> 00:52:41.230
But

00:52:41.230 --> 00:52:42.230
He did one thing

00:52:42.230 --> 00:52:43.230
Quite quickly

00:52:43.230 --> 00:52:44.230
And that was

00:52:44.230 --> 00:52:46.230
He built a masjid

00:52:46.230 --> 00:52:48.230
He built the first masjid

00:52:48.230 --> 00:52:49.230
With his own hands

00:52:49.230 --> 00:52:51.230
And the companions helped him

00:52:51.230 --> 00:52:52.230
And that is masjid Quba

00:52:52.230 --> 00:52:54.230
If we go to Madinah Munawwara

00:52:54.230 --> 00:52:55.230
We will see it

00:52:55.230 --> 00:52:57.230
And they built a simple structure

00:52:57.230 --> 00:52:59.230
So that the Muslims could pray

00:52:59.230 --> 00:53:01.230
And so that they could gather

00:53:01.230 --> 00:53:02.230
And so that they could meet

00:53:02.230 --> 00:53:04.230
And so that they could learn

00:53:04.230 --> 00:53:05.230
More about their faith

00:53:05.230 --> 00:53:07.230
And they built a structure

00:53:07.230 --> 00:53:09.230
Which was not a beautiful structure

00:53:09.230 --> 00:53:11.230
But the hearts of the people

00:53:11.230 --> 00:53:13.230
Who attended were beautiful

00:53:13.230 --> 00:53:14.230
Today it's the opposite

00:53:14.230 --> 00:53:16.230
Structure is beautiful

00:53:16.230 --> 00:53:18.230
Are the hearts of the people

00:53:18.230 --> 00:53:20.230
Who attend as beautiful

00:53:20.230 --> 00:53:21.230
May Allah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:53:21.230 --> 00:53:22.230
Grant us guidance

00:53:22.230 --> 00:53:23.230
Until we meet again

00:53:23.230 --> 00:53:24.230
And may Allah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:53:24.230 --> 00:53:26.230
And bless our prophet Muhammad

00:53:26.230 --> 00:53:27.230
Glory be to Allah

00:53:27.230 --> 00:53:28.230
Glory be to Allah

00:53:28.230 --> 00:53:29.230
And praise be to you

00:53:29.230 --> 00:53:30.230
We bear witness that there is no god but you

00:53:30.230 --> 00:53:31.230
We seek your forgiveness

00:53:31.230 --> 00:53:32.230
And we repent to you

00:53:32.230 --> 00:53:33.230
Praise be to Allah

00:53:33.230 --> 00:53:35.230
The Lord of the worlds

00:53:35.230 --> 00:53:38.230
The Merciful, the Merciful

00:53:38.230 --> 00:53:41.230
Owner of the Day of Judgment

00:53:41.230 --> 00:53:43.230
It is You we worship
